title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a medium saucepan cook milk, sugar and vanilla until soft ball stage.
Take mixture off heat.
Beat in peanut butter with mixer on high speed.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix
first 5 ingredients together.
Then mix in rest of ingredients.
Put in 2 regular bread pans, greased and floured or 4
small
pans.
Bake
at
for 1 hour.
For chocolate zucchini
bread add 2 squares of melted chocolate and decrease the baking powder to 2 teaspoons.

title: special occasion salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender.
Serve with your favorite combination of salad ingredients for a green salad.
Top with croutons.

title: easy cinnamon twists
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll each biscuit into a 9-inch rope.
Pinch ends together to form a circle.
Dip biscuit circle into melted butter, then in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Twist each biscuit to form a figure 8.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parsley buttered new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Place potatoes and water in covered microwave-safe dish.
Cook on full power in the microwave, 8-10 minutes or until fork tender, stirring once.
Drain water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to combine.
Microwave for 45 seconds on full power.
Place potatoes in serving bowl and pour sauce over them.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: gingerbread delights
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate 6 hours or more.
Roll on floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 9 or 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove, cool and decorate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the last two. Put in a long baking dish.
Spread the cheese over the mixture, then add the potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: loney mae's chicken and dressing
directions: Layer chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Add milk.
Mix stuffing with butter and chicken broth. Spread over top.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain all fruit thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients, sour cream last.
You can add more sour cream or a little syrup from fruits if you prefer it a little soupy.

title: best-ever corn bread
directions: Mix together egg and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 425°.

title: old fashion coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs and blend well. Stir soda into buttermilk and add to creamed mixture alternately with flour. Blend well after each addition. Bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. The batter fits into three 9-inch pans or four 8-inch pans. Frost with Mile High cake icing.

title: yummy cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook meat.
Salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, approximately 5 to 8 minutes more.
Cool 5 minutes. Bake at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Heat juice to boiling and mix with Jell-O.
Let set up some and mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add small amounts of milk until the batter is thin enough to be picked up by a spoon without running off.
Let batter sit for 15 minutes and stir again.
Scoop up a heaping tablespoonful of the batter. Push the batter off spoon with another spoon into hot oil.
Let fry until golden brown.
(May be cooked along with your fried fish.)

title: joyce higdon's chicken in wine
directions: Cook chicken, wine, soy sauce and water in a crock-pot on High for 2 hours.
Then add sugar, ginger and garlic.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cook rice in broth.
Serve chicken over rice.

title: chip beef ball
directions: Cut dried beef in pieces.
Combine all ingredients and form a ball.
Refrigerate. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: onions on the grill
directions: Select	flat
white onions, one per person.
Place each onion on	a
square
of heavy foil.
Cut 2/3 through in an X. Stuff
1 teaspoon butter into the X.
Sprinkle generously with lemon pepper.
Seal
foil and place on the grill.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Have all ingredients at about 75°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and hot water.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Then add extract and poppy seed.
Mix well.
Grease tube pan, then sprinkle pan with sugar and cinnamon, coating well. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: prize pan am coconut lime pie(in honor of hoosier horse review)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine water, cornstarch and ReaLime; mix well.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks; add to ReaLime mixture.
Add the cream of coconut; mix well.
Over medium heat cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peak forms; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry. Spread on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Top with coconut.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool.
Chill before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook everything except oatmeal.
Once it comes to a boil, cook for 3 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in oatmeal.
Drop quickly by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray bottoms of muffin tin cups with Pam spray or line with baking cups.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in cereal.
Combine bananas, milk, oil and egg.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: grits casserole
directions: Boil water, salt and grits until stiff. Add butter and garlic cheese roll to cooked grits.
Break eggs in measuring cup and fill with milk.
Mix thoroughly and pour into casserole.
Top generously with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Combine celery, pickle, diced eggs and dash of pepper to tuna.
Mix salad dressing more, if needed, to tuna mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaf or crackers or make sandwich.

title: cocoa cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine sugar and cocoa, mixing well.
Set aside.
Whip softened cream cheeses, sugar, cocoa-sugar mixture and vanilla, mixing on medium with electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in egg substitute; pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla; carefully spread over cheesecake.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool; remove rim.
Chill.
Calories 291, fat 11 g and sodium 386 mg.

title: turkey or chicken salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss with Miracle Whip mixture.

title: harvest corn
directions: Mix melted butter, dill weed and other spices; toss with other ingredients.
Spread popcorn mixture on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rice and peas
directions: Combine rice and chicken broth in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook 20 minutes. Add peas (defrost, if frozen) and cook until peas are tender, about 2 minutes. Season with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: citrus mint cooler
directions: Place first five ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover; remove from heat and let steep until cool.
Strain.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, fill glasses or pitcher with equal amounts of fruit juice, ginger ale and water.
Add ice and serve.
Yields about 15 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with pepper and onion.
Drain.
Place meat on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix cheese and soup.
Spread over meat.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Be sure Tater Tots are done.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Add melted chocolate. Blend well.

Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add alternately with water to peanut butter-chocolate mixture. Pour into 3 (8-inch) greased layer pans or a 10-inch greased tube pan. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, until done, about 30 to 35 minutes for layer pans, 55 to 60 minutes for tube pan.
Cool and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: salem tea
directions: Mix tea with a small amount of water.
Add sugar and juice. Fill with water to make a gallon.
Mix well.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Run tines of fork lengthwise down side of unpared cucumber. Thinly slice cucumber and onion.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt; pour on cucumber and onion in glass bowl.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Drain and serve on crisp salad greens.
Equal sweetener may be substituted for sugar.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Sift self-rising flour into bowl.
Fill bowl about half full. Make a hole in the center with your hand.
Take 2/3 cup of water or chicken broth. Work into flour by pouring it into the hole and mixing loose flour with it.
Knead the dough well.
Take ball of dough and roll it out on a floured brown paper or whatever you have to roll it out on (any flat, clean surface, sprinkled with flour).

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook egg yolks, milk, flour, sugar, oleo and vanilla in double boiler until thick.
Fold into this mixture the 3 egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Line casserole with vanilla wafers, then layer of bananas, then pudding; repeat until all ingredients are used.
Place wafers on top of last layer of pudding.

title: avocado crab or shrimp salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water, vinegar and salt.
Set aside.
When starting to set, beat until foamy.
Mash avocado and mix with softened cream cheese.
Mix celery, green pepper, pimento, onion juice, mayonnaise and eggs; add to foamy jello.
Add avocado mix to jello.
Add crab or shrimp.
Pour into Pyrex dish and refrigerate.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Combine yeast, warm water, sugar, salt and egg in a large bowl; set aside for 5 minutes. Gradually add 3 cups flour, beating well. Add oil, then add remaining flour to form a stiff dough. Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes). Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover with plastic wrap. Let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until doubled in bulk (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion together.
Drain and put in a baking dish. Top with potatoes and then corn.
Pour soup over this and bake until potatoes are done.

title: nana's ice tea
directions: Bring water to boil. Turn gas off and place tea bags in water. Let steep a few minutes. Squeeze and remove tea bags. Add sugar and stir.

title: carrot cake
directions: 1. Mix and bake about 50 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13 pan greased and floured. Don't overbake.

title: mother's banana nut muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add bananas, milk, vinegar, vanilla and nuts, alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: In large saucepan, bring the soup and water to a boil.
Add rice; stir.
Cover and remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Add cut up turkey and peas to the rice mixture.
Reheat and it is done.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and slice apples, then dice, leaving the red outer peel. Cut celery, first cut a stalk in 3 or 4 long strips, then cut on the bias across several strips at once, making thin one-inch lengths.

title: mushroom patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into patties.
Fry in oiled pan until brown.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and sour cream. Sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture.
Add extract.
Roll out thick; cut with cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° until brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water (according to package directions). Add cranberries to hot water and break up with fork. Then add only 1 cup cold water. Add remaining ingredients. They will float to the top, but this gives it a layered effect.

title: italian rice pie(easter)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Cook the rice in 1 1/2 cups water for 20 minutes in covered saucepan.
Rinse with cold water; drain and add to mixture in large bowl.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) Pyrex pie plates.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
For doneness, check for golden crust or bubbling mixture.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Cook noodles; add to meat. Add soup, milk and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: kielbasa stew
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add the cut up kielbasa, potatoes and tomatoes with the rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour in crock-pot and serve with a warm bread.
Yum!

title: easy party reuben sandwiches
directions: Cook corned beef in crock-pot for 8 hours.
Add a little water and stir in intervals so the top doesn't get tough.
After 8 hours, drain and shred beef.
Mix together cheese, sauerkraut and salad dressing.
Add this to the meat and heat until the cheese melts.
Do not overheat.
Serve over rye or black bread.

title: danish goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch cubes.
Brown well in hot oil with pepper.
Add onions and stir until light brown.
Add salt, 2 1/2 cups water, sugar and bay leaves.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/4 hours or until fork-tender.
Remove bay leaves.
Stir in flour that has been mixed with 5 tablespoons water.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Stir up real well.
Put in baking pan and cook at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
Layer chicken with cooked and drained vegetables.
Mix together mayo, soup and lemon juice. Spread over chicken mixture.
Add cheese to top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and use enough Miracle Whip salad dressing to your taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: inexpensive fruit cake
directions: Mix syrup, shortening, flour, brown sugar, egg, cocoa and black coffee, then add nutmeg, cinnamon, ground cloves, raisins, peanuts, ginger, raisins and chopped prunes.
Mix well and bake in greased and floured pan.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add in flour and mix well.
Add in nuts.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies do not spread.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not let them brown.
Cookies can be rolled in powdered sugar before completely chilled.

title: cocktail meat balls with sauce
directions: Beat egg; add salt, pepper and bread crumbs.
Add beef and minced onions; mix well.
Heat chili sauce, jelly, lemon juice and vinegar in a large pot over low heat until jelly melts and mixture is well blended.
Form meat mixture into small balls; drop into chili mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to be sure none is stuck on bottom and all are covered.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes or until meat balls are done and sauce is thickened.
If frozen, reheat slowly.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes, pepper and onion, then add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: crab cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then fold in crab meat and crackers.
Drop by spoonfuls onto floured pan.
Sprinkle flour on top of crab cakes.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then fry until golden brown.

title: no-bake rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water, salt and oleo in a nonstick saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir; simmer and let cook 15 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes.
Stir in condensed milk, plain milk and raisins.
Bring almost to a boil over medium heat.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add some of the hot rice mixture, then add to rice mixture in saucepan.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes on low heat, then add vanilla. Continue cooking on low until thick.
Stir often.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bone.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and melted oleo.
Pour over chicken and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake slowly for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: greens with rice
directions: Rinse greens thoroughly.
Cut stems into 1/2-inch pieces. Chop leaves.
Heat oil in a heavy saute pan over medium heat.
Add onions; saute 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add stems; saute 2 minutes.
Add leaves.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until wilted.
Add garlic and rice; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with greens.
Add water. Cover and cook over low heat, without stirring, until rice is tender, about 18 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve sprinkled with toasted almonds.
Makes 2 to 3 main dish servings or four side-dish servings.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice, omitting bulbs.
Transfer to large bowl and cool. Add pepper, onions and olives.
Drain artichokes; slice and add to rice.
Mix all with liquids, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Chill and serve.

title: good muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
To dry mix add eggs, milk and melted Crisco.
Mix until moist.
Spray muffin pan with Pam and fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 good size muffins.

title: ham loaf
directions: Form 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: brunch special
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Remove cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: french rhubarb pie
directions: Put
rhubarb
mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Cover with topping.
Bake
at	400° for 10 minutes.
Continue baking at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Mix soda in sour cream.
Set aside. Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs then chocolate, flour and sour cream with soda, alternately.
Bake either in loaf pan or two layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: steamed cranberry holiday pudding
directions: Cut cranberries in half.
Rinse cranberries and raisins; drain well in colander.
Place in mixing bowl.
Sift flour and soda over fruit.
Add molasses and water; stir batter until smooth.
Turn into a 2-quart greased and lightly sugared pudding mold.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil and place on trivet in deep kettle.
Add enough boiling water to come halfway up the sides of mold.	Steam, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Cool to lukewarm and turn out on cookie tray.
Serve with warm sauce.

title: bloody marys
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yield: 5 quarts.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: *Other frozen juices can be substituted.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Then put all together in pan with vinegar, sugar, spices and peppers. Boil 20 minutes.
(Spices can be tied in a bag if you do not want them through the pickles.)
Bottle and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: kay's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter.
Combine sugar, apple pie spice and salt.
Mix all well and stir in beaten egg.
Fold in apples.

title: cran-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water; add cranberry sauce and mix well until dissolved.
Add applesauce; stir and mix well. Pour into mold, if desired, and chill.

title: ginger carrots
directions: Heat carrots and water to boiling in 10-inch skillet.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain; remove carrots from skillet.
Cook and stir butter, honey, lemon juice, ginger and salt in skillet until bubbly.
Add carrots. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, milk and oats in bowl and mix well. Shape mixture into meatballs.
Brown on all sides in butter in skillet.
Transfer meatballs to casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Saute onions until tender. Add cream cheese and shrimp.
Cook until warm throughout.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Put in loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch babies("breakfast treat")
directions: In a blender, mix egg for 1 minute.
Add half and half, then rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter into deep dish pie pan.
Pour batter into dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and jelly, freezer strawberry or raspberry is best.

title: strawberry angel food trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in large bowl.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until blended.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture, then stir in pecans.
Add this mixture to cake cubes and mix well.
Spoon cake mixture into trifle bowl. Spread strawberry pie filling evenly on top or, if desired, layer half the cake mixture and pie filling; repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate at least three hours before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix onion, bell pepper and sausage together.
Saute these with butter; drain.
Add baked beans, syrup or honey, ketchup, mustard and sugar; mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflowerets in salted, boiling water until just fork-tender.
Drain.
Put into a greased baking dish.
Add soup, mixed with water.
Add cheese, cut in cubes.
Spread crumbs, dots of butter and more cheese cubes over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until edges bubble and crumbs are a golden color.

title: basic cake batter
directions: Mix sugar & Crisco until smooth. Add eggs one at a time. Alternate flour & milk until mixed well. Add vanilla and blend well. Bake at 325° for 30-45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, then well beaten eggs. Add lemon juice and rind.
Mix well and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and then oil together.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Gradually stir in flour, cocoa and soda, mixing well. Stir in zucchini (raw and grated).
Sift cinnamon, ground cloves and salt, stirring to blend well. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: Melt half of margarine; add chicken with Tony's and brown slightly.
Add chopped onions and bell pepper.
Saute, then add rest of margarine and 1 cup uncooked rice.
Stir constantly until rice begins to brown slightly.
Add 2 1/4 cups of hot water, additional Tony's and mushrooms.
Cover.
Reduce heat and cook until rice is done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: beach cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix next two ingredient.
Add confectioners sugar and blend.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fudge puddles
directions: In mixing bowl cream oleo, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 48 balls, 1 inch each.
Place in greased mini muffin pan.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes or until browned.
Remove from oven and immediately make wells in center of each by lightly pressing with small melon ball.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes then carefully remove to wire rack.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Cook onion in oleo; place 1/2 potatoes in buttered casserole and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add part of onion and grated cheese.
Mix sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour half over potatoes.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and sour cream until smooth. Add other ingredients and crumbled Bleu cheese.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and line with whole graham crackers.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, combine pudding and 3 cups milk at medium speed.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture on graham crackers.
Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Top with remaining pudding.
Top with third layer whole graham crackers.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients and confectioners sugar.
Spread over top layer of crackers.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Makes 15 servings.

title: plain dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water or cake yeast in lukewarm water. Add milk, sugar, shortening and salt in a large bowl.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg. Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well. Cover; let stand in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn out on floured surface; shape as desired.

title: salmon mousse(delicious!)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water
in
a
large mixing bowl. Stir in the boiling water and
whisk the mixture until gelatin dissolves.	Cool to room
temperature.
Whisk
in
the Miracle Whip, lemon juice, onion, Tabasco,	paprika,
salt	and
dill. Refrigerate for
30 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Fold in the salmon.
Whip the cream and gently fold into mixture.
Put in 6 to 8 cup bowl or mold; cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve with crackers, toast or black bread. Can
be served
as
a main course, garnished with watercress. Serves 12 as an appetizer and 4 to 6 as main course.

title: pa-pa's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except blueberries.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Add blueberries.
May add additional 2 teaspoons sugar, if desired.
Use 8 or 12 section muffin pan.
Grease. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mint moo
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Blend until the mixture is smooth.
Makes 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain (should be about 3 cups).
Stir butter or margarine into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie plate as a crust.
In skillet, cook ground beef or sausage, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn meat "mixture" into spaghetti crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into
small
balls.
Press with a fork. Cook at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: lavender bath gel
directions: Pour into a jar.
Seal and store in the refrigerator.
Use 1/4 cup per bath.
You may put some on a washcloth to use in the shower, if you prefer.

title: nutty carrot salad
directions: In a bowl toss the carrots, pineapple, raisins, sunflower kernels and peanuts.
In a small bowl combine peanut butter, yogurt, mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over carrot mixture and stir gently to coat.
Serve in a lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 4.

title: mama's rolls
directions: Mix yeast, grease, sugar, water and salt.
Add flour until dough is very stiff.
Grease dough and let set until it rises. Break off and set in a deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine peaches, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract, cinnamon and 1/4 cup water. Turn into baking dish (8 x 8 1/2-inch).
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with batter.

title: baked salmon cheesecake
directions: Butter spring-form pan with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter (if pan leaks, cover outside with foil).
Mix bread crumbs, Gruyere and dill; sprinkle evenly over bottom of pan.
Press into pan. Refrigerate.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and hot sauce.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into glass baking dish.
Spread evenly.
Toast at 400° for about 20 minutes.	Salt when you remove.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften to room temperature.
Mix well. Add garlic, salt and Worcestershire sauce and mix again. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Shape into balls and roll in parsley and pecans.
Chill.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Add beef to water in a 4-quart pot.
Stir until beef separates into a fine texture.
Boil slowly for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Serve with bowls of cooked spaghetti, chopped raw onions and grated cheese.
Chili can be refrigerated overnight so that the fat can be lifted off before reheating.

title: daddy's sauce for fish or dip
directions: In small bowl, combine sour cream, vinegar, salt, cayenne and grated onion.
Mix thoroughly then gently stir in the chopped dill and diced cucumber.
Taste; it might need more salt.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, Karo and butter in pan and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over 7 quarts of popped corn.
Put in 250° oven and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Butter pan before adding popcorn and syrup.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not sift flour and don't drain the pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blender broccoli soup
directions: Partially thaw broccoli.
Place in blender with 1/2 cup of milk.
Blend until fine.
Add remaining milk, cream, onion, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth.
Heat on stove.
Add cheese and simmer.

title: layered green salad
directions: This salad is made in layers and is best to use a plastic container with top so you can refrigerate overnight.

title: hasty cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add milk. This makes a pouring dough.
Stir well.
Put margarine in the baking pan and set in oven to melt and get hot.
When hot, remove from oven.
Spread dough all over and around in the hot margarine. Have your fruit in another pan, let it come to a boil, then pour over dough while all is hot.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Crush up chips and mix it all together just before serving.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg, blending well.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.

title: aunt irma's cream spread
directions: Heat milk over medium heat.
Add flour and stir until this forms a ball and leaves the side of the pan.
Let cool.
Cream sugar, butter, shortening, salt and vanilla together until smooth. Add flour/milk mixture to this.
Chill.
This is wonderful to spread on pound cake and add strawberries.

title: non-fattening banana cake(for diabetics)
directions: Mix in a large bowl with spoon.
Pour batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan before removing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix with broccoli.
Add 4 beaten eggs. Stir and add cottage cheese, salt, cornbread mix and Cheddar cheese.
Stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: corn pone
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Combine flour, yeast, salt and sugar in mixing bowl and stir. Add vegetable oil and water.
Mix together all ingredients.
Knead by hand for 3 minutes; shape and put in bowl. Cover and let rise until double in volume (approximately 1/2 hour).
Punch down; divide into 2 equal pieces and shape into round balls or leave in one piece for 16-inch pizza.
Let dough rest for 4 minutes.
Roll out approximately 12 or 16-inches in diameter.
Spray pizza pan lightly with no stick vegetable cooking spray and wipe off excess. Place on pizza pan; let rise for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sauce, toppings and cheese.
Place on bottom rack in cold oven; turn oven to 500° and bake 17 to 20 minutes, depending on oven.

title: savory baked game hen
directions: Cut hens in halves; clean.
Place hens on baking pan, bone side down.
Mix other ingredients well and brush or spoon on hens. Bake at 350° basting hens with juices and remaining mixture until done.
Serve with rice pilaf or saffron rice.
Serves 6.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add brown sugar and caramelize into ground beef.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, salt, pepper, diced onion, crushed garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon cubes and bay leaves.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chris' potatoes
directions: Heat until smooth, stirring, the cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and oleo.
Add and mix thoroughly the sour cream, cheese, onions and thawed hash browns.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion in butter until onion is clear. Add soup, tomatoes and crawfish. Cook 1 hour.

title: quick curried chicken
directions: Saute chicken and onion in margarine in a skillet until chicken is
tender.
Stir in soup and curry powder.
Cook over medium
heat,
until bubbly.
Add sour cream; heat thoroughly. Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: karen's frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, stirring all the time. (Looks like mashed potatoes.)
Let cool until cold.
Cream the sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add to cold mixture and whip with an electric beater.
Looks like whipped cream.

title: italian chicken over spaghetti
directions: In roaster, combine chicken pieces and all ingredients, except Mozzarella, Provolone and spaghetti.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir and top with Mozzarella and Provolone.
Cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Mix well and serve over spaghetti.
(Let stand 15 or so minutes before serving and stir again before serving.)

title: summer chicken salad
directions: On salad plates, arrange spinach leaves, chicken, fruit, celery, almonds and green onion.
In cup, mix together mayonnaise and orange juice.
Drizzle over chicken mixture.
Garnish with orange slices and strawberries.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cinnamon roll mixture
directions: Mix together and use with basic sweet dough to make delicious rolls.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and sugar in top of double boiler or in microwave.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, cornstarch, then other ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean-corn salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hot mexican-style fish
directions: Place frozen fish on 20 x 12-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Seal securely.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet in 450° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn back foil and pour margarine over fish. Sprinkle with salt.
Top with salsa and olives.
Cook, uncovered, until sauce is hot, about 10 minutes.
Serve with lemon or lime wedges.
Yields 5 servings.

title: slow-cooked lamb chops
directions: Wrap bacon around lamb chops; secure with toothpicks. Place in slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove chops; discard toothpicks and bacon. Drain liquid from slow cooker. Add potatoes and carrots. Top with lamb chops. Sprinkle with rosemary, garlic powder, salt, pepper, onion and minced garlic.

title: cannelloni
directions: Mix well in a food processor or with a hand mixer.
Cook crepes in a Teflon pan.
Cool with paper toweling between each crepe.
The crepes may be wrapped in plastic wrap and frozen at this point.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry and drain meat.
Fry and crumble bacon; add beans.
Add brown sugar to taste.
Heat in crock-pot.
Good leftover.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Crumble bread slices and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Grease pan or spray (with Pam).
Pat out meat loaf in pan.
Add catsup to top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or microwave for 12 minutes.
Turn halfway and cook about 8 minutes, depending on how large the meat loaf is.

title: reynold's marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots, onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
In a medium size saucepan heat together sugar, oil, vinegar and tomato soup.
Pour this over the carrot mixture.
Store covered in refrigerator overnight and serve cold the next day.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer until thick.
If too thick, add water. Small chunks of pineapple may be added for different flavor.
Add a couple of drops of food color for color.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix everything in a casserole dish. Add broth and half of the cheese.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brahm's simply wonderful cranberry sauce
directions: Place cranberries in an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish (or same sized baking pan).
Sprinkle sugar evenly over berries.
Dribble cognac over sugar.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: To make poppy seed dressing, mix vinegar, sugar, onion, salt and mustard in a blender.
Slowly add oil and chicken broth.
Stir in poppy seeds.
Toast pecans; cool.
Dressing and pecans may be made 1 to 4 days ahead.
For salad, mix spinach, celery and strawberries.
Toss with 1 cup dressing.
Garnish each serving with 1 Tbsp. pecans.
Extra dressing may be kept 1 week and is great over fresh fruit.

title: pepper steak with tomatoes
directions: Partially freeze meat (20 to 30 minutes).
Slice paper thin and sprinkle with paprika.
Brown meat and garlic in hot margarine in a skillet.
Add water, soy sauce and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions, green peppers and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in blended cornstarch and cook and stir gently until sauce is thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and stir until blended. Grease two 9-inch pie pans.
Divide mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gingerbread boys or girls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Stir in egg, syrup and vinegar; beat well.
Chill.
Roll in pecan size balls using 3 balls for each boy or girl.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press one ball with thumb to flatten for head, roll one into straight "rope" for arms and another for the legs.
Use raisins or red hots for eyes and buttons.
I like to use confetti cake decor because of the color and they do not melt like red hots.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Meat Sauce:
Saute onion and ground beef. Drain. Add tomato sauce, Chili-O mix and beans.
Season with salt and pepper. Add picante sauce. Simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: wife's dream
directions: Get into car, go to nearest restaurant and stuff themselves. It's truly a wife's dream.
Serves 2 or more.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Cube cheese on top.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers. Sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven 25 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Brown bacon until crisp and crumble.
Mix onion, mustard, Cheddar cheese and enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
Cut French bread into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Spread mixture on slices and cut into 9 squares per slice.
Place squares on cookie sheet and place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Stir in ice cream and spices. Pour into shell and put into freezer.
Before serving, put on whipped topping.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles and drain.
Add milk, butter and drained tuna.
Mix well.
Add in cream of mushroom soup and mix.
Add in half of the Mozzarella cheese and half the Cheddar and mix.
Place in a casserole dish and add remaining cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable soup(low-fat)
directions: In a large soup kettle, heat olive oil and saute garlic, onion and barley until onion is translucent.
Stir in vegetables (except cabbage and mushrooms, if used).
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add parsley.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 40 minutes, or until vegetables and barley are just tender. Stir in tomato puree.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Add cabbage and mushrooms now, if you are using them.
Simmer 15 more minutes or until vegetables and barley are completely tender.
Adjust seasonings.
Just before serving, sprinkle each portion with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients very well. Add melted butter and milk. Put pan on heat and slowly add milk stirring as you do. Cook stirring constantly until thick like gravy. Serve with biscuits.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya(wally's favorite)
directions: In a large pot on medium-high heat, saute chicken, sausage and garlic in small amount of oil.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until tender (a little wilted).
Add 2 cups of water and Creole seasoning.
Add bay leaf, oregano and 3 cups of water. Stir well.
Bring to a boil and add rice.
Stir.
Cover and turn to low for 30 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
Cover and cook longer if needed.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour half the batter in greased pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fiesta punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine lemonade concentrate, pineapple juice and sherry.
Add ice.
Just before serving, pour in champagne.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons of water. Stir into sauce.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover; simmer until done.

title: puffy potato doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in butter, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar on lukewarm water; stir to dissolve.
Add yeast, baking powder, baking soda, mashed potatoes, egg yolks and 2 cups flour to milk mixture.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Or, beat with spoon until batter is smooth. Gradually add remaining flour, blending well.
(Dough will be soft.) Place in lightly greased bowl.
Turn dough over to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 2 hours.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine bouillon broth, cornstarch and soy sauce; blend well. Stir in scallions and set aside.
Heat oil in wok and stir-fry chicken and garlic, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove and keep warm.
Add broccoli and broth mixture to the wok.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes. Add the chicken and pimentos and heat just until mixture is good and hot.
Top with sesame seed.
Serve over pasta or rice.
(May substitute pork for chicken.
Makes 6 servings.
Calories 153, fat 4.l g.

title: peanut butter ho ho cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to the directions on the box. Let cake cool completely.

title: pasta with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Add celery, onions and garlic. Cook lightly. Add flour and stir until incorporated. Lower heat. Add cream and stir until blended.
Add clams and broth.
Partially cover skillet and cook at lowest heat for 10 minutes.
Add parsley.

title: texas mocha cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and egg.
Mix cocoa, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk, brewed coffee and vanilla into the creamed mixture. Bake at 350° until done when tested, approximately 30 minutes for 2 layer cake.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute.
Stir until golden color (8 minutes approximately).
Combine onion, bouillon and salt in medium saucepan; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cranberry stuffed cornish game hens
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Mix all together and stuff in hens.
Place hens in baking dish; baste with the last 3 ingredients.
Baste while baking.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Check after 1 hour.
Very tasty.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill crusts and chill about 3 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for egg whites.
Beat egg whites, but not too stiff.
Fold egg whites into dough.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator. Roll
in
balls and pat out with fingers or can roll out and cut with
cutter.
Sprinkle
with sugar.
Take off pan as soon as they are done.
Bake at 350° until they start to brown around edges.

title: quick guacamole
directions: In a bowl, mash the avocado.
Stir in cottage cheese and picante sauce.
Add jalapeno if desired.
Serve with chips or vegetables.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: mabel's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients in the given order until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: autumn chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, fry bacon and onion.
Drain grease.
Add potatoes, carrots, chicken bouillon
and water to cover.
Boil and then simmer for 20 minutes (until potatoes and carrots are soft). Add half and half,
corn and pepper.
Heat until warm. Do not boil.
Add cheese
and
stir until melted.
Soup should be thick like a stew, if
not,
add in a small amount of flour dissolved in water to thicken.

title: bible cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making a boy in 1 Proverbs 13:24 (he that spareth his rod hateth his son, but he that loveth him chasteneth him betimes) and you will have a good cake.

title: mexican pork chop dinner
directions: Sprinkle salt in large skillet.
Add chops and brown over medium heat.
Sprinkle chili mix over chops.
Add rice, water and tomatoes.
Be sure rice is moist.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.

title: linda ridel's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Combine oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder. Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: mocha balls(yields 100 servings)
directions: Melt chocolate; let cool.
Beat yolks.
Add sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Beat in butter.
Dissolve coffee in brandy and add vanilla.
Combine brandy mixture with egg and butter mixture.
Add chocolate and mix thoroughly.
Chill well.
Shape into balls and roll in chopped nuts, coconut, powdered sugar or anything that suits you.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Drain. Combine other ingredients. Pour mixture over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika for color. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes on High.
Freezes well.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Add Miracle Whip to other ingredients until it spreads like you want it.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add sugar to water, stirring to dissolve.
Add fruit juices; chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 6 to 8 servings or 1 1/2 quarts.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, Parmesan cheese and milk well.
Add all remaining ingredients except the lettuce; mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce beds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts thoroughly. Spread mixture in a 9 x
13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, syrup and salt to a boil in a 2-quart bowl.
Boil 2 minutes on High in microwave oven.
Remove from oven. Stir in soda.
Put corn in large grocery sack without any writing on sack.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Shake and mix well.
Fold over top of bag and place in microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes. Remove bag from oven every 30 seconds and shake.
Spread caramel corn on waxed paper to cool.
Store in tightly-covered container. Don't let sack touch oven.
Watch so won't catch fire.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Set power select at High.
In a 3-quart pyro-ceramic casserole dish, heat water and butter 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in sugar and molasses.
Heat 13 to 14 minutes or until mixture reads 300° when tested with candy thermometer.
Quickly stir in peanuts and baking soda, stirring it until soda foams.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Let stand until candy is hardened; break into small pieces.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not drain pineapple tidbits. Chill and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Place in a 300° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until heated through.
Meanwhile, spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add red pepper; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes more, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add oil to skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes, or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add salsa; cook and stir until heated through.
To serve, divide chicken mixture evenly among tortillas. Top with shredded lettuce.
Dollop with yogurt; sprinkle with green onion.
Roll up tortillas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and water in a medium saucepan. Bring to a full boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix very well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: potato dippers
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Cut each potato half lengthwise into 3 wedges.
Arrange potato wedges in a spoke circle on a large microwavable platter.
Melt margarine for 30 seconds in the microwave.
Brush potatoes with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cover with wax paper. Cook in microwave for 7 minutes on High.
Turn the platter halfway around.
Microwave for 8 minutes.
Remove wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes immediately.
Serve with the prepared party dip.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water; set aside.
Mix sugar, walnuts and cinnamon together.

title: brownies(yield: 24 brownies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar until it forms a soft ball (about 6 minutes).
Stir
all the time, take from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until stiff.

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and flake the crabmeat.
Add crab to cream cheese mixture along with chopped green onion.
Turn into a greased 8-inch pie plate or small, shallow baking dish.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated all the way through.
Keep spread warm over a candle warmer.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef.
Mix with water and sauce. Pour 1 cup of mixture into lasagne pan.
Layer 1/2 of noodles.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Put 1/2 of Mozzarella and cottage cheese/egg mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat sauce, noodles and cheeses.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 1 hour at 400°, covered with foil.

title: jello balls(candy)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into balls and chill.
When firm, wrap individually in plastic wrap or dip into chocolate.

title: golden crumb broccoli casserole
directions: In covered saucepan, cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimiento and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with the cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough into pizza pan or disposable pizza tins and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix well cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla extract and Cool Whip.
Spread on dough.
Arrange kiwi, bananas, strawberries, oranges and any other fruit you prefer on cream cheese mixture.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Roll into the 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch deep-dish pie pan or shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of pan.
Mix chili and salsa until blended.
Then pour over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: bonnie hillyer's hot ryes
directions: Mix ingredients. Spread on rye or pumpernickel bread. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly in skillet, then drain.
Crumble bacon.
Saute onion in bacon fat until brown. Blend in skillet, flour, sugar, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Carefully stir in potato slices and crumbled bacon pieces.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.

title: dixie stew
directions: Combine grapefruit juice, salt and garlic.
Add beef cubes and refrigerate overnight.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
Heat oil in skillet; brown beef on all sides.
Add green pepper and onion and saute 3 minutes.
Add tomato.
Combine marinade with brown sugar, vinegar, rosemary, cayenne and bay leaf.
Add beef and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until beef is tender.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended. Add eggs; mix until blended. Stir in 1/3 cup of chips. Pour into crust and top with remaining chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, applesauce, oil, eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, nuts, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add to applesauce mixture and beat until well combined.
Stir in nuts. Turn batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake in a 305° oven for 1 hour.
Cover loosely for last 30 minutes.

title: good and spicy meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat egg slightly.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add ground beef; mix until combined. Shape into tablespoon-size meatballs.
Place in a single layer in greased or foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until well browned.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add mustard and honey.
Stir until mixed.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Pour honey mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: mom's pickled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to boil.
Pour over eggs and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: carolina coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 370°. Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet or 9-inch square baking pan. Cream shortening and sugar together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in milk. Stir in flour and pecans; blend well. Pour batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle evenly with crumble topping. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan. Cool in pan for 15 minutes and drizzle with confectioners icing. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift next 4 ingredients and combine with creamed mixture.
Chill dough overnight.

title: cheese, bacon and mushroom-stuffed burgers
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix cheese, mushrooms, bacon, onion and mustard.
Shape 12 thin patties.
Put 1/4 cup cheese mixture onto center of each.
Top with second patty; firmly press edges and seal.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This is good with all raw vegetables.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes. Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Add sour cream and vanilla. Beat until well blended. In large bowl with lid, fold in grapes and nuts until well covered. Refrigerate overnight.

title: corned beef cheese balls
directions: Mix chopped corned beef, chopped onions (whole onions) and softened cream cheese.
Add Accent, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix again.
Shape into 2 balls or 1 large ball.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.
Can be made the day before you want to use it or you can wrap and freeze it.

title: spinach and rice(a favorite rice dish alone or with meat)
directions: Rinse fresh spinach.
Remove and discard stems.
Chop leaves. If using frozen, thaw and squeeze dry.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook for 20 minutes. Add mushroom soup.
Melt the cheese and stir in.
Serve with chips.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients to make the dressing.
Pour dressing on and toss salad about 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and butter well in small bowl.
Press into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add grated cheese, chopped onion and peppers.
Set aside.
Mix cornmeal, oil, eggs, soda, salt, milk and corn.

title: cold pasta and chicken primavera
directions: Cook pasta al dente in boiling water; drain and transfer to a mixing bowl.
Add 1/3 of the dressing; toss.
Let cool and chill for 3 hours.

title: vanilla wafer fruitcake
directions: Chop fruit and nuts, reserving 4 whole cranberries, 16 pecan halves and 2 slices pineapple.
Mix chopped fruit and nuts with wafer crumbs.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Add fruit mixture, mixing well.
Let stand while preparing loaf pan with waxed paper.
Pack in pan.
Decorate top with cherries, pecan halves and pineapple.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread(jamaican recipe)
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add egg; mix
well.
Add sifted ingredients.
Bake in waxed paper lined loaf
tin in moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 70 minutes. Chopped nuts (1/2 cup) or raisins may be added.

title: christmas eggnog pound cake
directions: Light oven.
Get out bowl, spoons and all ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Crack nuts for filling.
Remove 18 blocks and 7 toy autos from kitchen table.

title: beef roll
directions: Mix together 4 packages of dried beef, cream cheese, onions, sauces and Accent.
Make into 2 rolls, using waxed paper.
Roll in the remaining 2 packages of dried beef.
Wrap in foil and chill. Best if left overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Heat to boil; remove from heat.

title: meringues
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Spoon mixture into piping bag and pipe shapes onto baking sheet lined with greaseproof paper.
Bake at 130°C for 60 minutes.
One pound = 453.6 g.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until brown (about 15 minutes at 350°).

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: *Heaping teaspoonfuls recommended for seasonings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and wring out water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out bread and fill with dip.
Use the bread from the center of the loaf for dipping.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip together the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: stuffed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and bake potatoes	at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Peel and
mash
potatoes
and banana.
Add oleo, orange juice and salt.
Put	into
baking
dish;
cover
with pecans. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: deep dish cherry-peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, 1 cup oats, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup mixture and combine with 1/4 cup oats.
Cut in 1/4 cup margarine until crumbly; set aside.

title: sour cream spinach
directions: Cook frozen spinach as
directed
on
box.
Drain well. Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add cooked spinach; stir to keep from sticking.
When
well
heated,
add mushrooms and sour cream. Heat for 2 minutes and serve.

title: fried devil dogs
directions: Blend Crisco, egg and milk.
Mix seasonings and baking powder with the flour.
Dip wieners into fine crumbs, then into batter made from flour.
Heat Crisco to 375° or when an inch cube of bread browns in 60 seconds.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cheese; mix and add milk and bread crumbs. Cool slightly.
Mix; add onions, green peppers and squash.
Mix. Put in well-greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle bacon on top. Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans and bake at 325° until done.

title: stevee's chocolate mousse
directions: Place medium mixing bowl in freezer to chill.
Melt chocolate chips. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy, sprinkle in sugar and keep beating for 3 minutes (until eggs are thick and very light in color).
Scrape chocolate into egg mixture.
Beat until just blended.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Preheat broiler. Spray 8 x 8-inch pan and a 10 x 10-inch piece of aluminum foil with vegetable spray. Peel and slice eggplant in 1/4 inch thick slices. Place on cookie sheet and broil 2 or 3 minutes on each side. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 375°.

title: company best pickles
directions: Cover whole cukes with boiling water.
Allow to stand until next morning; drain.
Repeat this procedure on the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces. Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar; bring to boiling and pour over cukes.
Let stand 2 days.
On third day, bring to boiling and seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 7 jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute bacon, onion, celery and peppers until soft.
Transfer to 1-quart casserole.
Add all ingredients; cover with additional cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and crusty.
When a knife is inserted and comes out clean, then the casserole is done.

title: peanut butter party mix
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Toss in cereals and peanuts; stir until coated.
Spread mixture on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°, stirring once.
Turn out on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: mrs. o. j. york's pecan roll
directions: Put sugar and Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Mix until all of sugar is used up.
Add vanilla.
Knead as biscuit dough.
Divide in 4 parts.
Roll on wax paper in 1 long roll.
Cut in small pieces.
Melt caramels over hot water.
Hold the pieces between forefinger and thumb; roll in pecan pieces.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool slightly.
Add frozen orange juice, stirring to melt.
Chill until slightly runny and add pineapple and oranges.
Pour into shallow pans or mold.
Chill and serve on lettuce, topped with mayonnaise.
Serves 10.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine tomato sauce, green pepper, chili powder, chopped onions, bouillon cube and garlic powder and simmer 10 minutes. Add cooked beef or turkey, Cheddar cheese and cooked rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Place in sprayed baking dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heavenly 24-hour salad
directions: In small saucepan, mix eggs with sugar, orange juice and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and salt.
Cool, then fold in sour cream.
Chill while preparing fruits.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Put ammonia between paper and pulverize, then put in milk and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not use that which doesn't dissolve.
Add other ingredients and enough flour to roll well. Cut and bake at 300° to 350°.
Over 100 years old.

title: briar patch bake
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Stir in barbecue sauce and onions.
Heat.
Prepare macaroni according to directions on package except use 1/2 cup milk.
Layer half of dinner in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining dinner.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda, and salt. Make a well in the flour mixture and add 2 eggs. Stir together. Stir in vanilla and oil. Add pie filling and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 10x13 pan.
After cake is done, drizzle with glaze.

title: chili flavored shrimp
directions: Mix together butter, chili powder and garlic powder.
Dip shrimp in mixture and wrap each with 1/4 slice of bacon.
Cook on barbecue grill 5 minutes on each side.

title: bean curd with oyster sauce
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or large skillet over high heat. Add bean curd and stir-fry until light brown, about 3 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Combine water, oyster sauce, cornstarch, sherry and soy sauce in small bowl.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in wok or skillet over high heat.
Add all vegetables, stir-fry for 1 minute.
Return bean curd to wok; toss lightly to combine.
Add cornstarch mixture to wok.
Cook and stir until liquid boils.
Cook for 1 minute more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage broccoli chowder
directions: In a skillet, cook and crumble sausage until no longer pink. Remove to paper towels to drain; set aside. In the same skillet, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender; set aside.

In a Dutch oven, cook the broccoli and carrots in chicken broth until tender. Stir in sausage and the mushroom mixture. Add soup, tortellini, pepper, basil and thyme; heat through. Stir in cream and Romano cheese; heat through. Yield: 12 to 16 servings (4 quarts).

title: mabel's chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter and add bell pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Add grated onion and flour, mixed with part of the milk and then the remaining milk.
Stir until thickened and add the chicken and remaining milk with egg yolks beaten in.
Cook a few minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add a few drops of lemon juice and the seasonings.
Stir in the green peas.
Serve in patty shells or on toast!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spoon into muffin pan and bake at 400 until brown.

title: spicy oven fried chicken
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat with corn meal mixture. Place chicken, skin side up, in large shallow pan.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake in preheated oven (375°) for about 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar together very well.
Add heated milk slowly.
Add vanilla.

title: cucumber dills
directions: Mix dry Good Seasons dressing with cream cheese.
Spread cream cheese mixture over the rye bread.
Place a skinless piece of cucumber on each piece of bread over the cheese.
Sprinkle the dill weed over the cucumber slices.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Measure sifted flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
Add salad dressing, warm water and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. thomas' cake
directions: Pour boiling water over cocoa and butter.
Mix together and add milk and sugar.
Add after sifting together, flour, soda and salt.
Beat well, then add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice with favorite fudge frosting.
(Keeps well.)

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Using a large, shallow pan, stir in sugar and cornstarch, mixing well.
Add vinegar, cloves, ketchup, oil, salt and vanilla. Stir well.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the beet juice.
Discard the rest. Cut beets into bite size pieces and put in pan.
Cover over medium heat three minutes, stirring until it thickens.
Serve warm when used in salads.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and fry.
Drain and pat with paper towels. Trim off bread crusts and cut into cubes.
Place bread crumbs in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage and cheese.
Mix mushroom soup, eggs and milk and pour over the layers.
Cover; let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake the next day, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix together beef, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Shape into 24 balls.
Make batter of eggs, flour and remaining teaspoon of salt. Dip meat balls in batter.
Heat oil in a skillet and brown meat balls over low heat.
Remove meat balls from skillet.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons oil.
Add green peppers, broth and pineapple.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Mix together cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Stir into skillet ingredients and cook until thickened.
Return meat balls and reheat 5 minutes over low flame.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking soda and peanut butter.
Add flour and oatmeal. Butter cake pan and pat in for crust.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Top with chocolate chips.
When melted, spread.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: double pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange drained pineapple slices and cherry halves on sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on the label with 1 1/3 cups water and 2 eggs.
Do not substitute pineapple juice for water.
Beat as directed.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes until tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand 5 minutes for topping to begin to set, then turn upside-down on a large platter or a cookie sheet.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add the sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, wine and chopped fruit dredged in flour.
Drop by teaspoon on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with comino and garlic salt in skillet.
Drain. Reduce heat to low.
Add 1/2 of Velveeta.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spoon 1/4 cup of meat mixture into tortillas and roll up. Place, seam down, in baking dish.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in large bowl. Add pasta and blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: party punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer a few hours before serving.
Should be slushy.
Add a few drops of food color, whatever color you want.

title: cherry chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain and cut water chestnuts in half. Cut bacon in 2 to 2 1/2-inch pieces.
Wrap around water chestnuts; secure with toothpicks.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Mix catsup and brown sugar until well blended.
(May need more sugar, so there is no vinegar taste.)
Pour over water chestnuts and bake 20 to 30 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop bake
directions: In skillet brown pork chops; drain.
In greased 2-quart baking dish arrange potatoes, then pork chops.
Add onion if like, then add soup mix thoroughly blended with water.
Bake, covered, 1 hour or until potatoes are tender (350°).
Yields 4 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and mayonnaise in bowl and chill.
Just before serving, fold in nuts.
Serves 4.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery in a skillet; drain off excess fat.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except the shredded cheese and cooked macaroni shells.
Let it simmer until mixture thickens, then put into a 3-quart casserole dish over the macaroni.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: easy bake rice and mushrooms
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake one hour at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well
and
pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown onions in butter.
Mix all the rest of ingredients.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat thoroughly.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate mixture.
To dry ingredients, add alternately the chocolate mixture and buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and then set aside until later. Combine in saucepan Bisquick, milk, salt and margarine.
Cook until thickened and add chopped onion and shredded cheese.
Add broccoli last.

title: best gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add boiling water last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until foamy. Beat in cornstarch and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla at high speed until stiff,
but not dry. Bake until golden, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix everything together, but cheese.
Pour half of mixture into greased pan.
Add grated cheese; then rest of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Form dough into balls (approximately 1-inch in diameter) and roll just the top in sugar.
Press lightly with fork and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown around the edges.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Saute onion in shortening about 5 minutes.
Mix onion with all other ingredients and shape into balls; fry in butter or oil. Drain and place aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted boiling water until tender.
Saute carrots and onions in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Mix 1 1/2 cups dressing bread, soup, sauteed carrots and onions and sour cream together; fold in drained zucchini.
Use remaining 1/2 cup dressing bread for topping.
Bake in moderate oven until heated through.

title: grilled new potatoes
directions: Cook or microwave small new potatoes until barely tender. Thread on metal or bamboo skewers.
Brush lightly with oil; season with salt and pepper.
Grill 10 to 15 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: mary's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut and press, or roll out for cookies.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers and spread in bottom of dish, covering bottom good. Salt and pepper chicken to your taste.
Mix together the soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with a few more Ritz crackers. Bake 1 hour.

title: hobo stew
directions: Divide ingredients equally in 8 individual 10 ounce custard cups.
Place ingredients in the cup in the following manner:
1 teaspoon water per cup, peas, potatoes, carrots and meat.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spoon over meat, making sure meat is completely covered.
Cover each cup with plastic wrap. Poke 6 holes in plastic wrap.
If 4 cups are being cooked at once, cook for 9 1/2 minutes, placing cherry tomatoes on last 1/2 minute. Let stand for 5 minutes.
If 3 cups are being cooked at once, cook for 8 minutes, placing cherry tomatoes on last 1/2 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
If one cup is being cooked alone, cook for 5 minutes, placing tomatoes on last 1/2 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate first 5 ingredients overnight in refrigerator.
If sticky the next day, add a little oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and place in favorite bowl.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, wine vinegar and sugar together.
Add to the broccoli, bacon and onion.
Add more mayonnaise if it is dry.

title: very best potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with peelings.
When done, dice up and add remaining ingredients.
Let chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Dissolve soda in coffee and add cocoa.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour alternately with coffee mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make 2 large or 3 small layers.

title: mexican pick up sticks
directions: Combine onion, potato sticks and peanuts. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Drizzle with melted margarine and stir. Sprinkle with taco seasoning and mix well. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes. Yields 2 quarts.

title: alice's easy peanut butter balls
directions: Place 1 package of chocolate coating in top of double boiler (over water on bottom of boiler).
Heat water to begin melting chocolate.
Mix all other ingredients together with hands.
Roll into small, tight balls.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: 3-day salad
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, seal tight and let stand at least 3 days.

title: cheese dip or sandwich spread
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
