This may be used either as a dip or sandwich filling, depending on the amount of mayonnaise added.
Keeps well when covered and refrigerated.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Put all in large pan.
Add chili powder; simmer for about 1 hour or longer.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In large skillet, over medium high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken, a few pieces at a time, until browned on all sides. Remove chicken pieces to roasting pan as it brown.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon fat from skillet and cook onion until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar, salt and 1/4 cup water; heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken in roasting pan.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until chicken is fork tender, occasionally brushing chicken with juices in pan.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, apples, pecans and other dry ingredients well.
Add eggs, slightly beaten, and oil last.
Toss until mixed. Do not stir or mix in electric mixer.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in tube pan.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil small potatoes whole in skin until done.
Cool somewhat and peel.
Mash potato with fork and slowly add xxx sugar, a small amount at a time, until you use up the box of sugar.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Should be a stiff ball.
Roll it out on wax paper using a little xxx sugar if sticky on wax paper.
Spread peanut butter all over the top.
Roll up jell-roll style and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Slice in 1/2-inch thick (or less) and serve.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: rich yeast batter
directions: Mix together the milk, sugar and salt; crumble yeast into mixture.
Add egg and shortening; stir until shortening is melted. Add flour and beat for 1 minute, at least 100 strokes.
Scrape down from sides of bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise at 85° until double in bulk (about 1 3/4 hours).

title: old fashion brownies
directions: In bowl combine sugar, eggs, butter, Nestle Choco Bake and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and add one 9 or 13-ounce bowl of Cool Whip and 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter; stir in powdered milk.
Knead until well mixed.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.

title: heavenly lush
directions: Mix together and place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: sweet-and-spicy pecans
directions: Toss pecans in butter.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients; sprinkle over pecans, tossing to coat.
Spread pecans on a baking sheet; bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely.
Put 2 tablespoons margarine or butter (melted) in glass pan.
Place mushrooms in pan, top up.
Mix crab (shredded into small pieces), egg, mayo, lemon juice and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Stuff mushrooms. Cover with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Beat together sugar, egg yolks and soft butter.
Add flour. Mix well.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Blend in batter mixture.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until set (or done).

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pudding mix with juice.
Add fruit cocktail and Cool Whip. Add pecans.

title: "genuine bananas foster"
directions: First melt butter, then add brown sugar until sugar melts. Add bananas and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir for approximately 1 minute; then add Triple Sec and serve over ice cream.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices and arrange on cookie sheet, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Let cool.
Pour liquid from oranges and pineapple into saucepan.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch and cook until thick.
Set aside and let cool.
Spread mixture of cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and teaspoon vanilla onto cooled cookies.
Arrange fruit in layers, pineapple, oranges, bananas, strawberries, etc.
Pour cooled sauce on top to cover all fruit.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dr. pepper baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from pork and beans; pour into baking dish.
Gently mix in onion, pepper and tomato. Combine sugar, Dr. Pepper and cloves until sugar is dissolved. Pour evenly over bean mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge frosting
directions: Sift together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and milk until of desired consistency.
Stir in peanut butter.
(This is a good frosting for Wacky Cake.)

title: herb grilled kabobs
directions: Heat grill.
Arrange meat and vegetables on skewers.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place kabobs on grill over medium-high coals.
Brush with dressing mixture.
Grill 10 to 15 minutes or to

title: beef stew
directions: After you have browned the stew meat, put in a pot and add potatoes, carrots and onions, with enough water to cover and cook until tender.
Add peas with juice.
Put cornstarch in a cup with salt and pepper; add just enough water to make a liquid.
Pour into stew and cook until thickened.

title: hacienda bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler and heat until cheese melts and dip is warm.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Before you begin on First Layer, wash and halve the strawberries.
Pour sugar over strawberries and let stand to sweeten.

title: cheesey potato casserole
directions: Pour hash browns in 9 x 13 pan. Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over hash browns. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: thousand island dressing(diabetic recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; mix with a fork until smooth. Place in a covered container; refrigerate until served, using 2 tablespoons per serving.

title: grammy's cucumbers and cream
directions: Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well and then add cucumbers and onion.
Refrigerate until serving time. Makes about 8 or more servings.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, milk, cocoa, and butter for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, peanut butter, and oats. Mix together and spoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool before eating.

title: vegetable stuffing
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and celery in bouillon. Add other vegetables and cook partially.
Add bouillon as needed to keep moist. Add garlic powder and pepper.
Stuff turkey.
(Or bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.)

title: honey-citrus pork chops(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Place pork chops in flat baking dish.
Combine orange juice, lemon juice, honey, dry mustard, light salt, pepper, allspice, ginger and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour over pork chops and marinate several hours, turning once or twice.
Place pork chops and sauce in broiler about 6-inches from heat, basting frequently with sauce. Cook 15 minutes on each side until well done.

title: chocolate-nut rice krispies squares
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes longer.
Remove from heat. Add chips and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with a buttered spatula.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli 3 minutes in microwave, let cool.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine
oil,
sugar,
eggs, flour and flavorings.
Add apples and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Delicious warm or cold.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil jalapenos for about 10 minutes and snip stems off.
Place all ingredients in an airtight jar and let season for 7 to 10 days.
Great for deer camps.
Serves 1 to 24.

title: chocolate ice cream brownies
directions: Prepare
brownie mix according to package directions in a 13 x 9	x
2-inch
pan.
Let cool in pan.
Spread ice cream over brownies.
Freeze until hardened.
Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients
in
a	saucepan.
Bring
to a boil, then reduce heat to	medium.
Cook
an
additional 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir
in vanilla and pecans.
Cool.
Spread frosting over ice cream.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Brown meat and remaining ingredients.
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes

title: daddy's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs; stir in wafer crumbs, coconut, pecans, cherries, vanilla and milk.
Put into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or until done.

title: apple crisp #2
directions: Place apples and water in a baking dish. Sift flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon into a bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix vinegar, cheese, lemon juice, oil and water.
Put in chicken and marinate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Remove chicken and put in baking pan with potatoes.
Pour half the marinade over the chicken and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and add the rest of the mixture, baking for 15 more minutes.
Next, turn the chicken again and sprinkle the raisins in the pan and bake for 15 more minutes. Carrots may be substituted for potatoes.

title: devil's island eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Mash yolks; add bacon and dressing.
Mix well.
Refill egg whites.
Garnish with pimento or parsley.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add cornstarch and sugar.
Beat in melted butter and vanilla.
Add pineapple.
Pour into unbaked pie shall and bake at 325° until set.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Arrange peaches in dish and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of peaches.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth. Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion. Mix well. Separate dinner rolls into 4 rectangles. Firmly press together perforations to seal. Spoon 1/4 of the mixture into each center. Pull the 4 corners to the top. Seal all edges. Brush tops with 1 tablespoon melted margarine. Sprinkle on bread crumbs. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Serve with ruffled potato chips or Fritos.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the pumpkin, milk, cinnamon, vanilla, sugar, salt and eggs together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the dry cake mix and walnuts together; sprinkle over first layer.
Drizzle melted butter over the top; bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar, butter, shortening and eggs; add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: curried pecans
directions: Combine butter and seasonings.
Mix well, add pecans and toss well.
Spread on
ungreased 15-1/2 x 10-1/2 inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° 10-12 minutes stirring occasionally.
To serve warm, put in 350° oven for a few minutes before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with cream cheese.
Add fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour into cupcake pans.
Cover with wax paper.
Freeze.
Allow to thaw approximately 20 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix all
ingredients together, spoon into greased muffin tins or on buttered bread pan.
Bake at 350° or until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and mandarin oranges.
Slice bananas. Mix all ingredients into a bowl.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; put in a baking dish.

title: chicken with crabmeat and rosemary(real gourmet)
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a medium skillet over moderate heat.
Add bread crumbs and saute until browned, 2 to 3 minutes. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, pit and cut the avocado into 1/2 x 1-inch pieces; mix with the lemon juice and set aside. In

a large, heavy saucepan over moderate heat, melt the remaining butter; add the onion and saute until golden, about 5 minutes. Reduce the heat to low and stir in flour, paprika and rosemary. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until flour is lightly browned, 5 to 7 minutes; stir in the chicken broth and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens, about 5 minutes.
Remove the pan from heat and stir in sour cream.

Blend in the chicken, crabmeat, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Gently blend in the avocado pieces (with lemon juice) and turn into a 2-quart baking dish. Cover with the sauteed bread crumbs and bake 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with watercress sprigs, if desired, and serve.
Serves 6.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix well; shape into small balls.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in just enough water to barely cover until done. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Ready to eat on a cold winter night.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar, margarine and milk over medium-high heat until reaches rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and mix in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla. Pour in buttered 9 x 11 dish. Cut when cool.

title: mexican crinkles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls, then roll in sugar. Place
on
greased
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
If you don't want chocolate leave it out.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put breasts in a greased or sprayed baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired.
Top with sauerkraut and Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese. Cover pan with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, pickle relish, Russian dressing, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix with hands or wooden spoon to blend well.
On sheet of plastic wrap, shape meat mixture into a 7 x 14-inch rectangle.

title: plain banana pie(heritage)
directions: In an unbaked pie shell, alternate layers of bananas, brown sugar, flour, lemon juice and pats of butter.
Cover with a top crust.
Brush top crust with a mixture of egg yolk and water. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon-applesauce salad
directions: Empty candy into small saucepan with the water.
Heat over medium heat until candy melts, stirring constantly.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: lite bugle call chicken tenders
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine the skim milk and Ranch dressing mix.
Dip each tenderloin into the milk mixture and then coat with the crushed Bugles.
Place on a baking sheet that has been lightly coated with cooking spray.
Lightly spray each of the tenderloins with the cooking spray.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook until almost tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over beans.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: sour cream noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Brown meat in butter (if needed); drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and noodles.
Mix with meat.
Bake in a large dish, topped with cheese, for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll out thin, cut and bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Heat oven to 300° (low).
Grease and flour a 9 3/4-inch tube pan.
Blend butter and sugar in a large bowl; beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Gradually add eggs and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended.
Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Add nuts and raisins to flour.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture; blend thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Serve when completely cool.

title: complete breakfast
directions: Cook
sausage;
drain and crumble.
Spray pan with Pam. Mash rolls
into bottom of pan. Put crumbled sausage on top of rolls; put cheeses on top of sausage. Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour
over
cheeses.
Bake
at
350° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted into middle comes out dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, butter, syrup and 2 cups chopped nuts.
After beating put 1 cup whole nuts on top.
Bake at low temperature for about 40 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and dates.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and sides of pan (8 x 8-inch).
Save some of the mixture for the top. Chill thoroughly.

title: root vegetable casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and rutabaga 10 minutes, boil in large pan. Add other vegetables.
Boil, reduce heat cook 5-7 minutes.
Drain and return to pan.
In another pan melt butter, stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cook until bubbly, 4-7 minutes. Pour over vegetables and cook until hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in black skillet.
Cook until thick and add 1 stick margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together all but the last two ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top casserole with the corn flakes mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel icing
directions: Blend together all ingredients until smooth.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Stir strawberries and sugar in bowl. Bring water and Sure-Jell to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add berries and stir 3 minutes. Pour into 1/2-pint jars to within 1-inch of top.
Put caps on; screw bands tight.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours or until set, then freeze.
Yields 6 half pints.

title: chicken 'n' hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns overnight in refrigerator.
Layer in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place chicken and mushrooms over hash browns.
Stir together sour cream, broth, soup, bouillon, onion, red pepper and garlic. Sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: bell pepper-fresh corn pancakes
directions: Combine corn, egg yolk, cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold half of egg whites into cornmeal mixture, then fold in the rest.
(Do not overmix.) Coat medium-hot skillet with oil.
Drop batter into skillet. Spread round like pancake and cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: white layer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add salt, vanilla and lemon extract; beat well.
Fold in egg whites gently.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Top with favorite icing, fruit or strawberries.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: corn oysters
directions: Combine corn, eggs and cracker crumbs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and seasonings.
Add to mixture.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil in skillet (small amount of oil).
Fry until browned, about 3 minutes; turn once.
Makes about 18.
Serve hot.
Enjoy!

title: grape shine
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Put through a food mill to separate pulp.
Reheat jar and seal.
Cold water bath for 5 minutes.
Don't use paraffin wax or pectin.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into a mixing bowl and beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend and then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Ice when cool.
Cake can be baked in 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix into flour.
Add pecans.
Make small drops (approximately 1 teaspoon) of batter on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from sheet.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Brown hamburger meat and onions. Drain.
Drain potatoes.
Mix in milk and add ingredients.
Heat and serve.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until limp.
Drain and mix with condensed soup.
Place noodles and soup in a 3-quart casserole. Arrange chicken on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is tender.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Place meat in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add vegetables; cover with soup and milk.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven easy chili
directions: Brown beef with onion; pour off fat.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Cover bottom of a buttered 2-quart casserole with corn chips.
Pour in meat mixture; top with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hot bologna
directions: You will also need a 1-gallon jar.

title: broccoli with creamy lemon sauce(makes 2 servings; carb count: 5 grams)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli, in top of double boiler. Cook over simmering water 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring constantly. Serve over hot cooked broccoli.

title: nut clusters
directions: Place cream and Kisses in large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and margarine in pan; bring to a boil on medium heat. Pour over Kisses and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well blended. Add pecans.
Cool slightly.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving juice.
Blend reserved juice with sugar and cream cheese in bowl.
Combine strawberries, pineapple and remaining ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.
Freeze overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: primavera pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Heat oil over low heat; stir in all remaining ingredients, stirring about 3 minutes. Toss with pasta.

title: red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage; put in pan with salted water to cover and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Heat to boiling; cover and cook until tender. Drain.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain, keeping bacon grease in pan. Add to it brown sugar, flour, water, 1/4 cup vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thick.
Add sauce and diced bacon to cabbage.
Stir and heat through.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Put water, sugar and yeast in bowl.
Add salt and 2 cups sifted flour.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and melted, cooled lard and beat 1 minute.
Gradually add 4 1/2 cups flour, stirring until dough is formed.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out and cut each circle wedge like pie into 12 wedges.
Start at wide part of wedge and roll up to form rolls.
Put in pan and let rise.
Use beater for this recipe.
Bake at 375°.

title: wassail
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil; simmer.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Drain and cool.
Add next four ingredients.
Add Italian dressing to taste.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add zucchini and remaining flour. Beat well; zucchini becomes part of liquid.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: tuna cake
directions: Mix bread, tuna, egg, Worcestershire, mustard and salt. Shape mixture into 3 patties, about 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in oil over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Top with dill sauce.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Dice first 4 ingredients.
Grate carrot and radishes in food processor or blender.
Mix together with cooked macaroni.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and sugar and stir well.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Mix
together
pineapple
and
grated
cheese.
Combine together sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Mix in with pineapple and cheese mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers and layer top with crackers.
Cut margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry batter cake
directions: Wash and drain berries and press through ricer.
You can use potato masher.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine with egg, milk and butter.
Pour into 9-inch square pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use berries on top of cake.
Can use milk over all for shortcake dessert.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered jar.
Use within 6 months. Ingredients may be increased proportionally.
Makes enough for about 20 tacos.

title: roommate's tortilla soup
directions: In large saucepan mix all ingredients thoroughly and heat to serving temperature.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until foamy.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with wet ingredients and blend well.
Add pineapple, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: flakey pie crust
directions: Sift flour with salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine meal.
Sprinkle with water, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork until all of the flour is moistened. Form dough into ball; divide in half.
Roll each to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board; fit pastry loosely into pie plates. Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Trim and flute edges. Bake in preheated hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) crusts.

title: sweet fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Mix canned fruit and pudding mix. Refrigerate 2 hours. Add banana and serve.

title: creamed green bean soup(hungarian zoldbableves)
directions: Cook beans and onion in water until tender.
In a small frying pan, brown 3 tablespoons flour.
When browned, add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, whisk in a small amount of soup juice.
Stir mixture into soup.
Before serving, stir in 1/2 pint sour cream.

title: ebby's turkey dressing
directions: Break bread and crumble crackers.
Sprinkle baking powder over top of bread and crackers.

title: taco casserole in minutes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add chili powder and onion; mix well.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until onion is slightly cooked. Turn off heat.
Add crushed nacho chips.
Mix well in meat mixture.
Pour in tomato sauce and mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes. Turn off heat.
Place cheese slices on top until covered.
Melt cheese.
Add tomatoes and lettuce before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: gelatin jiggles
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in bowl. Pour into 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm, about 4 hours. Cut into 1 inch squares or use cookie cutters to cut into different shapes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300 degrees until done.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs, salt and sugar.
Scald milk; let stand and skim.
Pour into egg mixture; add vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top, also.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° hot oven; turn down to 325° for 35 to 40 minutes more, or until knife comes out clean.

title: bay green beans
directions: Mix beans in a saucepan; add butter, seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Let simmer for 10 minutes after coming to a hard boil. Wait for 2 minutes, cool down and place in bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Ready to serve.

title: lemon delight
directions: Blend margarine, flour and nuts and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and place on top of flour mixture.
Mix the pudding and milk and place on top of cream cheese mixture and add remaining Cool Whip.

title: chicken soup with herbed dumplings
directions: Put chicken in pot with broth, water, salt and Tabasco.
Bring to boil and skim off foam.
Reduce heat; add carrots.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Mix Bisquick, onions, basil, egg and milk in medium bowl until stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful into rapidly boiling broth.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 10 minutes, until dumplings have puffed.
Pull chicken off bone in large pieces and serve with soup and dumplings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no fuss fruit salad
directions: Mix canned fruit, peach juice and pudding. Mix. Refrigerate overnight. Add rest of ingredients. Chill until ready to serve.

title: california tossed salad
directions: Combine green, oranges, avocado, mushrooms and onion rings in a salad bowl.
Toss lightly.
Serve with dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Pour milk in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Using a hand egg beater, mix well until the mixture is foamy.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: Cut away the core of the cabbage. Cut the cabbage half into quarters. Cut each quarter crosswise into very thin slices. There should be about 6 cups of shredded cabbage. Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the cabbage. Add the cloves and salt and pepper to taste. Cook, stirring often, about 15 minutes. Do not allow to brown.

title: watermelon popsicles
directions: Seed the watermelon and puree it in a food processor or blender.
Pour into plastic popsicle molds or paper cups and freeze for several hours.
If you are using paper cups, wait until the popsicle is partially frozen, then insert a popsicle stick.

title: easy chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add pudding mix, cake mix and chocolate chips.
Bake in Bundt pan (lightly greased) for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool before removing from pan.
Enjoy!!!

title: rhubarb custard pie(amish recipe)
directions: Place chunks of rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until set.

title: chess squares
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Add one egg and beat together. Pour over cake mix and work together well by hand.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out to cover the bottom of the pan.

title: sour cream shrimp
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
In frying pan, cook mushrooms and scallions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add soup; cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour and pecans.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar, corn syrup, pineapple and vanilla. Pour into refrigerator dessert tray.
Freeze until firm.
Remove to chilled bowl; add unbeaten egg white and beat until fluffy. Return to freezer for 20 to 25 minutes or until frozen.
Serves 5.

title: chicken breasts with rice
directions: Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or cake pan.
Stir in dry onion soup.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Mix both soups and 1 soup can of water in a bowl.
Pour soup mixture over chicken breasts and rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes until rice is done.
You may need to pick up chicken breasts and stir liquid into rice about halfway through cooking.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix together nuts, flour and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: union station cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and melted chocolate. Put dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Add to creamed mixture. Add chocolate chips and pecans. Place golf ball-size pieces on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake only for 8 minutes. If you leave in longer, they will get hard. Smaller size cookies are better. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: martha stewart brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 8-inch square glass pan.

title: cheese date ball
directions: Blend in food processor or blender.
Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: macaroni veggie salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tomatoes oregano
directions: Cut tomatoes in half; cut six slices from each half.
Sprinkle liberally with next 3 ingredients.
Melt margarine; stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle tomatoes with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: This no-mayonnaise-or-cream potato salad is perfect for summer outings.
Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, in large serving bowl until well blended.
Add hot potatoes; toss to coat.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: peach pie in a pan
directions: Put peaches and 1/2 c. sugar in pan and bring to a boil.

title: watergate congealed salad
directions: Arrange a nest of lettuce.
On it place the drained pear half cup side down.
Make tail at larger end of pear with marshmallow. The head is the stem end.
Make mouth with cherry and eyes with raisins.
Long ears are made with long almonds.

title: pull taffy
directions: Heat first four ingredients in saucepan to hard crackle stage (260 degrees).
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well add pour into buttered platters.
Let cool just enough to be able to handle the heat.
Butter hands and pull taffy until it turns to pearl white ivory color.
Lay out in a rope and cut into bite size pieces.

title: twice-baked mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook until soft.
Drain and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish. Dot with butter.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° until potatoes are warm.

title: microwave fried potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Slice French fry style; drain and put in a baking dish.
Place onion on top of potatoes and slice butter on top of onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Cover and place in microwave for 10 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking for an additional 10 minutes.

title: low sugar bread for bread machine
directions: Follow bread machine instructions for mixing and baking.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
In skillet, brown beef and onions.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add buttermilk slowly.
Stir.
Add mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally, add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Stir in noodles.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: sour cream pound cake ii
directions: Bring the butter or margarine and eggs to room temperature. Grease and flour the bottom and sides of a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat the butter or margarine at medium speed of electric mixer until creamed.
Gradually add the sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat about 1 minute after each.
Scrape the bowl frequently with rubber spatula; beat 2 minutes more.
Stir together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Add lemon extract, orange extract and vanilla; beat just until thoroughly blended.

title: onion cookies
directions: Blend and shape into 4 rolls about 1 inch in diameter.
Chill or freeze; cut into slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mud hen bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in whole egg and two egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Combine the two mixes.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread batter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows over the batter.
Beat the two egg whites until stiff.
Fold in brown sugar.
Spread over top of batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: it's the berries pork chops
directions: Heat a large heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Brush each chop lightly with olive oil and cook chops for 9 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally, until evenly browned on both sides and just done.
Remove chops to a serving platter; keep warm.

title: sabena salad
directions: Part 1:
Dissolve Jell-O in juice from No. 2 can pineapple (heated then chilled).

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 7-Up and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in pineapple; put sliced bananas on top. Chill until firm.
Add Cool Whip on top.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook together brown sugar, butter and canned milk until thick and brown.
Add 1 cup milk, flour and egg yolk and cook until thick.
Put on meringue and bake until brown.

title: speedy stroganoff stew
directions: Simmer stew about 10 minutes.
Before simmering stew, add the wine.
Heat potatoes.
When stew is simmered, serve stew.
Put potatoes around edge of serving dish.
Serve with salad and dinner rolls.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken broth and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cream of potato soup and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cheese gradually and stir constantly or cheese will stick.

title: white icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler and beat with mixer over double boiler until forms stiff peaks.
Remove from heat and add 1 t. vanilla.

title: broccoli-carrot surprise
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
While broccoli is cooking, blend soup and flour; stir in sour cream.
Mix with broccoli and carrots.
Put in greased 1-quart casserole.
Melt butter; stir in bread cubes and poultry seasoning; spoon around edge of casserole. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: honey kisses(medenyaka)
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Grease two large cookie sheets and spoon the mixture to form round cookies approximately 1 1/2 inches apart.
Place 2 or 3 raisins on top of the kisses. Bake at 350° for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Check frequently until golden brown.

title: budget bake chicken
directions: Heat soy sauce with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add wine and scallions.
Arrange chicken in baking dish and spoon sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jeane ann's cinnamon, caramel or dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine scalded milk, sugar, shortening and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup of flour; beat well.
Beat in egg and yeast.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Knead; place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until double, or refrigerate for at least 2 hours or up to 5 days.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.

title: cokie's chicken and fruit salad
directions: Cook chicken, cool and pick meat.
Discard bones.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and onions.
Add this mixture to chicken with the rest of ingredients, gently adding oranges last.

title: empanadas
directions: Mix flour, cream cheese and butter.
Roll out dough and cut circles of dough about 4 inches across.
Put 1 teaspoon of pineapple preserves in each dough circle.
Fold the dough over, turnover style; crimp edges with fork.
Brush with egg white. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 5 inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Beat sugar and butter in a large bowl until creamy.
Add eggs and bananas.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Fold in walnuts. Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand while creaming shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, flour and next four ingredients. Add oatmeal.
Stir until mixed.
Bake at 375°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place rolls in bottom of casserole dish. Add cooked chopped ham or cooked, crumbled sausage (I prefer ham).
Spread grated cheese over this.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour beaten eggs and milk mixture over this.
Bake at 350° until eggs are set.

title: sand tart or christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour.
Put in a cool place 8 to 10 hours.
Roll out as thin as possible.
Beat the yolks of 2 eggs and a teaspoon of water together thoroughly.
Brush the top surface of the cookie dough with the egg yolk mixture either before or after cutting with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts, cinnamon, sugar, etc.
Bake in a moderate oven until edges brown (about 10 minutes).

title: blackwood hall muffins
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl. Add the shortening, egg and milk.
Stir with a fork until blended.
Rinse blueberries and drain them on paper towels.
Stir them into the dough until thoroughly mixed. Grease the bottom and sides of the muffin cups and fill 2/3 full with dough. Bake for 20 minutes.
Muffins will be golden brown when done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Makes 4 quarts dry mix.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli and noodles
directions: Slice broccoli stocks at an angle about 1/4-inch thick. Separate bunches at the end of the stocks. Set aside. Heat oil. Fry crushed garlic. Add sliced steak. Cook, but do not brown, over medium heat. Meat will leave juice in the pan. Add broccoli. Cover and steam until broccoli shrinks a little. Add soy sauce, sugar and salt. Add enough water if needed to make a small amount of sauce in the mixture, about 1/2 cup. Mix cornstarch with a little water. Add to broccoli mixture to thicken. Pour over noodles. Pepper the top. Cover until ready to serve.

title: thanksgiving beans
directions: Mix beans, bacon, chestnuts and soup.
Place in casserole. Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's butter cookies
directions: In bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour or longer.
Use wax paper on table and additional flour to knead parts of dough that you are using to roll out.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind the vegetables and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: grandpa pat's green apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix together cinnamon, sugar and flour.
Add this mixture to the apples, coating them well.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice as usual in 2 c. water, about 20 minutes or until water is absorbed. Stir in margarine or butter; allow to cool. Rice may be cooked a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cook tomatoes and seasoning with liquid for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and okra and low boil for 5 to 10 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: microwave parslied potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in quarters.
Combine potatoes and water in 2-quart microproof casserole; cover.
Cook 12 to 14 minutes on High, or until tender, stirring once during cooking time; drain. Add butter, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir until butter is melted.
Serve right away while hot.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Total cooking time: 12 to 14 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients except dressing and butter and put into a greased casserole dish.
Mix dressing and butter or margarine and sprinkle on top of broccoli. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta primavera(serves 8)
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place asparagus pieces and broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water; cover and steam for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in large skillet until tender.
Add carrot and chopped peppers and saute until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and drain.
Combine cream, broth, green onions, basil and salt in a medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain and place on a large serving bowl.
Add reserved vegetables, whipping cream mixture and mushrooms.
Toss.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepper.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add potatoes, onions and seasoning. Add tomatoes and water (use your own judgement as to how much water to use).
Cover pan and cook until potatoes are tender.
Mix flour with water and stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into meat mixture.
Stir and simmer until flour thickens stew.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fruitcake cookies(makes 12 dozen)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift all dry ingredients into flour.
Add eggs and flavoring to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Mix in fruits and nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: In medium size bowl, lightly toss fruits, raisins and coconut. Stir yogurt until creamy.
Add to fruit mixture.
Gently fold in yogurt until fruit is well coated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: jumbo shells with cheese stuffing
directions: Cook jumbo shells and drain.
Combine cheeses with beaten eggs, salt, oregano and pepper.
Fill shells.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place stuffed shells one deep in dish and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a wire whisk.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for weeks if it lasts that long.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Combine cereal, beef, celery, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce; mix well.
Put in baking dish; bake 30 minutes.
Top with remaining tomato sauce and bake 45 minutes.

title: coconut pecan candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Chill 30 minutes.
Roll into small balls.
Chill candy balls in refrigerator.
Mix CandiQuick by directions on package.
Take candy balls out of refrigerator and dip them in CandiQuick.
Place on wax paper until chocolate is dry.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind tomatoes.
Put 1 cup of salt over them and let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze out and mix with other ingredients which have also been ground up.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Put in jars and seal.

title: grandma wing's chocolate filling
directions: Cook slowly until chocolate melts.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cool, then beat until smooth.
Use to fill cakes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, water and salad oil.
Stir and heat thoroughly.
Pour over potatoes in bowl and mix well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix in order listed and store in refrigerator.
Keeps and keeps.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling in a 9x13 baking dish. Dump pineapple over cherry pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix. Dump coconut and nuts over top, if desired. Bake 1 hr. in 325 degree oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in 10 x 13-inch pan to cover bottom.
On top of this, put cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over top and 1 cup of nuts.
Slice butter and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tunaburgers
directions: Fry onion in a little butter until yellow (about 5 minutes). Add green pepper and celery and cook for 2 minutes.
Take from pan and add to tuna which has been crumbled in bowl.
Add crushed crackers, garlic salt, egg and soup.
Make into burgers and fry in same pan as used for onion, but add more butter, if needed.
Fry about 10 minutes until browned on both sides.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, shrimp and onion. Add Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce to taste. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry peach chutney
directions: Up to 1 week before serving, in medium saucepan, heat ingredients to boiling over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to simmer; cook 20 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 12 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, tear up bread and spread on bottom of pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spoon sausage on top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese over that.
Beat together eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray; heat one minute.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 batches until browned.
Remove.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Saute onion in oil in large skillet for 10 minutes.
Add meat and garlic salt; brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Uncover; cook 30 minutes.
Add to or spoon over cooked spaghetti.

title: college brownies
directions: Make brownie mix according to directions.
Stir 1/2 bag semi-sweet chips into mix.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: luscious apple dessert
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, salt and water in large pot. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove from broth; cool, debone and chop meat.
Set aside.
Strain broth and discard vegetables.
Refrigerate broth until fat rises to top; skim off.
Reserve remaining broth.
Melt 3 tablespoons of fat in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute; stir constantly and gradually add 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Cook until thickened.
Combine yolks and cream; stir well.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of the broth mixture into egg mixture.
Stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Saute mushrooms 2 minutes and add mushrooms, salt and chicken to cream sauce; stir well.

title: cream of mushroom chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken breast in a casserole dish.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
In saucepan, add cream of mushroom soup; fill can half full with water and pour in saucepan.
Add cayenne pepper, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Once well blended, pour mixture over chicken breast in casserole dish.
Let marinate in the oven on 275° for 20 minutes.
Serve on a bed of rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together.
Add mayonnaise and 2 salts.
Mix well.
Mix in crab meat.
Spread mixture on 6 halves. Bake at 350° until toasted brown.
Cut each muffin into 4 pieces.

title: navada beans
directions: Cook bacon and onions until onions are tender.
Combine with beans, catsup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and molasses.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy apple coffee cake
directions: Mix together: cake mix, pie filling and eggs.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with mixture of flour, sugar and butter or margarine that have been cut together until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers (sliced or small whole cucumbers) into jars cold.
Put pieces of dill on top of cucumbers in jar and pour warm solution over them.
Seal at once in preheated jars.
Let water boil over jars 10 minutes or order to seal in cold pack canner. If you have solution left over, store in a jar until your next canning. I prefer using dill seed.

title: dad's chocolate chip pancakes(yield: 12-14 pancakes)
directions: 1. Preheat pancake griddle.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine cake mix, cinnamon, allspice, eggs, pumpkin butter and water with an electric mixer until smooth; mix in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 13-inch by 9-inch jelly roll pan.
(The pumpkin butter is used instead of oil.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 28 minutes until it springs back to the touch.
Cool cake for approximately 30 minutes.
Then icing as follows.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika. Add water, oregano, parsley, onion, carrots, potatoes, soy sauce, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Sprinkle in Wondra flour and stir until thickened.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, syrup, salt and eggs.
Add butter and vanilla; beat well.
Put pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300° to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Pecans will rise to the top.

title: clam snack
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well. Grease muffin tins and fill to 3/4 full. Bake at 350°.
Batter keeps for 6 to 9 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pastor's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add to tomato juice in large saucepan.
Add 1 can water.
Add beans.
Add spices, except cayenne.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cayenne as liked 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place 1 cup potato, 1/4 of the rutabaga or carrots, 1/4 of the round steak, 1/4 of the raw onion, 1 tablespoon butter and salt and pepper on half of unbaked pie shell. Fold over.
Seal by moistening edge.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes; lower to 350°. Bake 1 hour longer.

title: short ribs and zucchini
directions: Brown ribs on both sides, drain grease.
Pour tomatoes and Italian seasoning over ribs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover, bring to boil for 5 minutes, then simmer until ribs are tender. Slice zucchini and place over ribs.
Simmer until zucchini is tender.
Serve on platter with zucchini and tomatoes around ribs.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat the last 5 ingredients together and pour over mixed corn. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Remove beet tops, leaving 1-inch stems and tap roots.
Wash beets; cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain, peel and slice beets.
In a saucepot, combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt and spices (tied in a cheesecloth bag); heat to boiling.
Add beets and onions; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Continue simmering while quickly packing one clean, hot jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers beets.
Cap each jar at once.
Process 5 minutes in boiling bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss gently to blend.

title: crock-pot orange chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Combine 2/3 cup of flour with salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, pepper and garlic powder.
Thoroughly coat chicken in flour mixture.
Place sweet potato slices in bottom of crock-pot.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Combine soup with remaining ingredients except buttered rice; stir well.
Pour soup mixture over chicken breasts.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours (high setting for 3 to 4 hours) or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Serve chicken and sauce over hot, buttered rice.
Yields 6 servings (about 3 1/2 quarts).

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook in 3-quart pan the sugar and light corn syrup until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and butterscotch chips while mixture is still hot.
Chips will melt.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: grape pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift
flour,
soda,
spices
and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add
sugar
gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add
egg
and beat well.
Add bananas, oats and nuts and mix
thoroughly.
Add
flour
mixture and blend. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets approximately 1 1/2-inches apart. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: stuffed giant shells
directions: Brown chuck, onions, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Cool. Stir in cheese, bread crumbs, parsley and egg whites.
Prepare shells ahead of time.
Cook in about a quart of water about 15 minutes.
Drain and stuff with cheese mixture.
Spoon a thin layer of sauce in a pan.
Put shells in single layer.
Pour remaining sauce on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan at 400° until bubbly.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour, margarine and pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: grandma gentry's date bar cookies
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add flour sifted together with baking powder and salt.
Add dates cut in half (pit removed) and pecans.
Be sure to grease and flour cookie sheet, 17 1/4 x 12 1/2 x 1-inch.
Pour mixture in pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle the colored sugar on top of mixture before baking.
Green and/or red combination looks pretty at Christmastime.
Bake slowly at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until firm to touch.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops until lightly brown and place in a flat dish. Cook pepper for 2 minutes.
Place pepper and sliced onion and 1 can tomatoes (with juice drained off and saved) mashed up.
Dilute Hunt's tomato sauce with the tomato juice from the whole tomatoes. Pour over chops and sprinkle with oregano and garlic salt.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Fold Cool Whip and condensed milk together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
Use about 1/3 cup of mixture in 1 cup hot water.

title: coconut shortbread refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Press dough into pan and chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 325° in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: cattleman's steak soup
directions: In large skillet, brown steak well in oil, drain and set aside. In a soup pot, melt butter and add flour, stirring constantly. Very slowly add water, one cup at a time, to prevent mixture from becoming lumpy.
Add carrots, celery and onion.
Add mixed frozen vegetables and tomatoes.
Add Accent, Kitchen Bouquet, beef stock base, salt and pepper to taste.
Add browned meat, cover and simmer on low for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Uncover after 2 hours of cooking to thicken.
Serve hot with corn bread and green salad.
A thick hearty soup for Texas men's appetites, served on a cold winter day!

title: sugarless chiffon pie
directions: Prepare pudding, using less milk than directed.
Prepare whipping cream, using 1/2 carton with the Equal when whipping. Fold into pudding; pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes, or until potato is tender. Stir in corn; remove from heat.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Stir in milk and next 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Gradually stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until soup is thoroughly heated. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together first three ingredients; add sugar and mix well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet. Chill 40 to 45 minutes.
Melt chocolate morsels over hot water. Dip balls into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: old fashion egg salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs and celery.
Cover and chill.

title: bread pudding
directions: Sprinkle raisins in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter bread on both sides.
Cut in half and overlap in pan.
Heat milk and add well beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat and pour over bread. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place pan in another pan of water.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until custard is set and golden brown.

title: microwave cocktail hot dogs
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, marmalade and chili powder.
Cover. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Cut frankfurters into 3/4-inch lengths.
Fold frankfurters into sauce mix.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes, or until hot, stirring once.
Lay out on platter and pass with toothpicks or cocktail picks.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add flour, salt and sugar to beaten eggs.
Scald milk and butter.
Add to egg mixture.
Add corn and mix well.
Place in a greased casserole dish in a
pan holding 1-inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Check to see if center is firm.
This recipe is enjoyed by Myrtle's Katie.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients with a fork.
Firmly press mixture on bottom and sides of 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.

title: mu shoo pork
directions: Mix pork with soy sauce, cornstarch and water.
Set aside. Mix sugar and water with sweet bean sauce and set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok and stir-fry pork for about 90 seconds or until color changes. Remove and set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok and stir in ginger root and onion.
Add lily flowers, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Fry 30 seconds. Remove and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok and heat.
Add sweet bean mixture and cook until it looks "shiny."
Add all other ingredients and coat well with bean sauce.

title: olive, cheese english muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients, except olives until smooth.
Stir in olives.
Spread on English muffins.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Cut into quarters.

title: shepherd's pie(aka "the ploughman's lunch")
directions: Boil potatoes and prepare mashed potatoes as usual, but keep them firm (not too much milk and butter).
Boil sliced carrots, not too soft, and leave on the side.

title: o-dream salad
directions: Dissolve lime and lemon jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: ham and potato soup
directions: In a kettle, gently simmer potatoes, celery and onion in water to cover, just until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain well. Return to kettle with remaining ingredients.
Simmer gently 10 minutes, stirring often, and serve piping hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together the butter and the sugar.
Add in the 2 eggs and mix a little bit more.
In a different bowl, mix the sour cream and baking soda together, then mix in the ingredients from the first bowl.
Now mix in the rest of the ingredients and pour into a buttered pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jackie kennedy's cucumber salad
directions: Make a marinade of all ingredients, except oil.
Pour over cucumber slices.
Cover and store in refrigerator; stir occasionally.
Before serving, add salad oil and stir well. Serves 2.
Each serving contains 30 calories.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown the chicken in hot oil.
As the chicken browns, remove it to a large saucepan.
Place the onions and garlic in oil and cook until golden.
Remove and add to chicken.
Drain the oil. Use the same skillet to mix the other ingredients.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook for another 30 minutes.
Turn occasionally.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: grilled swordfish with fresh tomato-herb salsa
directions: Bring medium
saucepan of water to a boil.
Add tomatoes and blanch for 30 seconds. Drain. Transfer to medium bowl.
Cover with cold water.
Cool and peel tomatoes. Cut in halves. Squeeze out juices. Chop tomatoes; transfer to bowl. Add herbs, shallot, vinegar and 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Can be made ahead.
Store at room temperature for a few hours only.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Peel 1/2 inch strip around the center of each potato and immediately place potatoes in a medium saucepan of cold water. Add enough additional water to the saucepan to cover the potatoes by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil until potatoes are easily pierced by a fork but firm, about 20 minutes; drain.
Do not overcook. Cover to keep warm.
Place the butter in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on HIGH until melted, about 5 to 10 seconds.
Stir in minced parsley and chives.
Pour the butter mixture over the potatoes and toss to coat.
Spoon the potatoes into a serving bowl.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Put apples into a heavy saucepan.
Reserve 4 slices for garnish.
Cook apples over low heat (without water), stirring occasionally, until tender.
Mash cooked apples slightly.
Mix sugar and flour.
Gently stir into apples. Turn into pastry shell.

title: bourbon carrots
directions: Slice carrots crosswise at angle.
Place in saucepan with butter, maple syrup, salt and lemon juice.
Simmer over low flame, covered, until tender-crisp.
Add bourbon.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 minute more.
Serve sprinkled with dill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili(serves 6 to 7)
directions: In a large pan, add tomatoes, kidney beans and seasoning. Heat to boiling.
Simmer.
Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Drain fat and add to other ingredients.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve and eat.

title: creamy squash
directions: Wash and slice squash. Cook until tender. Saute onion in oleo. After the squash has been mashed, add the onion along with the rest of the ingredients and heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes.
Cut into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing mix and add to artichokes.
Mix well.
Chill. Delicious with sourdough bread.

title: peach cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat in flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into pan and place fruit on batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-a-Roni as directed on box. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until honey colored.
Add scant teaspoon of dry soda.
Pour on well-greased baking sheet.
As soon as it has set, slip knife under edge and turn whole piece over.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add milk until mixture will pour into hot greased pan. (Heavy cast iron pan is best.)

title: chicken au vin
directions: Combine mushroom soup, chicken soup and onion soup (all undiluted).
Add wine and coat chicken with sauce.
Place chicken in a glass dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on high 16 to 18 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Rotate dish at 10 minutes. Allow standing time of 10 minutes.

title: tuna almondine
directions: Either scrub potatoes or peel. Slice and place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Dot butter on top. Pepper to taste. Place, uncovered, in microwave for 4 minutes on High. On stove, in 2-quart pan, place remaining ingredients and heat until cheese has melted. Pour over cooked potatoes and place in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. You can vary this by adding a small can of mushrooms, adding some frozen peas or both.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add pineapple.
Spoon in two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 2 (8 x 1 1/2-inch) or (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In a mixer bowl, beat shortening on medium speed of an electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat to combine well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each.
Stir in cooled chocolate and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and cold water alternately to beaten mixture, beating on low speed.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cook 10 minutes in wire racks.
Makes 12 servings.

title: almond caramel crunch snack mix
directions: Pour cereal in a large bowl; set aside.

title: cake frosting
directions: Beat all together the butter, Crisco, egg whites and confectioners sugar. Add milk slowly until thoroughly blended.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the mixture for top crust.
Put remaining crumb mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with combined Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter; spread evenly.
Crumble reserved mix over that. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: baked ham, egg and cheese casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix ham, bread and 1 cup of cheese.
(Mixture may be covered and refrigerated until the next day.)
In a medium-sized bowl, beat eggs with milk and nutmeg.
Pour over bread mixture and toss to mix.
Let stand 15 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Use butter to grease an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Turn bread mixture into prepared dish; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and the paprika.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until cheese is melted and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine cheese, butter, sugar, salt and soda.
Add onions, dill seed, egg and softened yeast.
Beat well to blend thoroughly.
Add flour; mix well.
Cover and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down and put in a greased loaf pan.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Brush with butter.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, water, shortening, raisins, carrots, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool (approximately 1 hour).

title: cajun black-eyed peas
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper. Add tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes, then add peas and cook 15 minutes. Add onion soup mix and Tony's. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip tomato slices in water.
Dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Put in Pam-coated pan.
Spray Pam on tomatoes, turn over.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients with just enough milk to make a rather stiff dough.
Drop by the teaspoonful into deep hot oil (350°) until brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Cook only a few at a time, turning frequently with a slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm in low oven while you cook the rest.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and bake in large baking dish for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and add grated cheese over top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted over top.
Serves 6.

title: canned tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions, celery, parsley and peppers until tender. Put through a sieve. Add sugar and salt. Make a paste of melted butter and flour. Blend with juice. Heat and add to jars. Process in hot water bath 2 hours or in a pressure cooker (pints 15 minutes or quarts 20 minutes).

title: mexican casserole(feeds 20 or more)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain off excess grease.
Add beans, tomatoes and soup.
In a large casserole dish, layer the corn tortillas, meat mixture and cheese. Use about 1/2 of each.
Repeat layers, ending up with the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: spinach casserole(aunt sue doughty)
directions: Salt, cook and drain spinach according to directions on box. Press all water out in a colander.
In a bowl, combine spinach, cream cheese and margarine.
Spread into small casserole dish. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes small casserole or double for 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: mclachlin chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Mix salt into crushed cereal.
Dip each piece of chicken into butter.
Toss chicken in cereal mixture. Place chicken pieces on cookie sheet.
Drizzle remaining butter and cereal mixture over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° (legs 1 1/2 hours, drumsticks 1 hour).

title: salmon and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, onion, celery, garlic, chicken broth, salt and marjoram.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cream, milk and margarine.
Combine flour and corn; stir into soup.
Heat, but do not boil, until slightly thickened.
Gently stir in salmon and heat through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook stew meat until almost done.
Add vegetables.
Cook until done.
Add soup last.
Ready to eat.

title: croissant french toast
directions: Pour over croissants.
Wait 10 minutes.
Flip croissants and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect bread pudding(reduced fat)
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in 8-inch round baking dish. Place dish in shallow pan of water.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados with fork.
Scrape tomato pulp into avocados. Mix with onion and other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with 2 pieces of crisp cooked tortillas.
The bright green slick skinned avocados have a better flavor, if they are available.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine water and sugar in small saucepan.
Add cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add berries and boil rapidly until they pop (about 2 or 3 minutes).
Chill.
Remove cinnamon stick and serve in relish dish or hollowed-out lemon cups. Yields 6 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Add other ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with marshmallows. Brown at 350°.

title: noodle hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Mix noodles and meat.
Stir in soup, water and cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ellen's holiday egg nog
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl, gradually adding sugar until thick and light (about 5 minutes). Stir in liquor.
Beat heavy cream in a large chilled mixing bowl. Gently fold into egg mixture. Stir in half and half. Chill in tightly covered bowl. Sprinkle nutmeg on top of egg nog before serving.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: In large bowl measure first 7 ingredients.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs slightly; stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir the rest of ingredients all at once.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Makes about 12.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in small amount of melted shortening in a large frying pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Spoon into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Wash beef roast.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour pepper and juice over meat.
Put onion on top.
Cook 10 to 12 hours on low setting.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Place ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in given order. Sprinkle top with the 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift and add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut, then roll in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown and still soft.
Let cool and get hard before eating.

title: toasted snack mix
directions: In a bowl combine oat cereal, Shredded Wheat, pretzels and nuts to melted butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and onion salt.
Pour gradually over cereal mixture, stirring constantly to blend evenly.
Spread in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Stir occasionally.
Let cool.
Store in an airtight container for freshness.

title: quiche
directions: Combine cheese and flour.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serves 6.

title: baked corn scallop
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add corn.
Mix with eggs and corn muffin mix.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add cheese.

title: arkansas wedding pie crust
directions: Combine oleo, pecans and flour.
Press in 10-inch pan.
Cook at 350° until light brown and let cool.

title: country baked steak
directions: Wrap above ingredients tightly in foil (put into serving portions).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat and onion (drain).
Pour in large casserole dish.
Add spaghetti sauce and noodles.
Mix well.
Top with pepperoni and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: nancy's soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a soup pot and put in enough water to cover all the ingredients.
Simmer for 3 hours and serve hot in individual bowls topped with Mozzarella cheese, grated.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Place a 9 x 13-inch pan in the refrigerator.

title: turkey hash
directions: Make brown gravy; cook meat (chop up).
Add meat and vegetables to gravy.
Cook until done.

title: tasty tarts
directions: Roll out pie crust.
Cut into 5-inch circles to fit muffin pans.
Flute edges.
Combine and beat the remaining ingredients except nuts.
Fill tart shells 3/4 full.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 15 minutes.
Place nut halves on top of tart.
Bake for 1 to 5 minutes longer or until set.

title: banana nut bread
