directions: Mix
ingredients together and pour into an oblong bread pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onions (may cook onions with squash).
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form into ball and roll in parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: shelly's special supper
directions: Cook noodles according to box.
In large Pyrex, layer 1/2 of cooked noodles, hamburger and 1 jar of sauce; layer on slices of Velveeta and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Repeat process.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts au gratin
directions: Brush the brandy over the chicken breasts and let them stand 15 minutes to absorb the liquid.
Then rub the salt, pepper and marjoram into the chicken.
Melt the butter in skillet and add the chicken.
Brown carefully on all sides over low heat.
Remove chicken and arrange in baking dish.
Keep warm.

title: mexi dip
directions: Layer all ingredients and serve cold.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Boil all together for 3 minutes.
(I keep a jar of this in my refrigerator at all times.
This is a time saver and excellent.)

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and chill for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: batter-dipped mushrooms
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Mix flour and seasoned salt.
Wash mushrooms and dip into egg and milk mixture.
Next, place mushrooms into flour and seasonings mixture.
Make sure to coat well.
Place mushrooms into hot deep-fryer (such as Fry Daddy).
Grease should be on about 300°.
Cook mushrooms 2 to 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Salt and pepper may be added to taste.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in light oil; then make gravy and set aside. In a casserole dish, put a layer of sliced potatoes, a layer of sliced onions, then potatoes and onions again.
Arrange chops on top.
Add soup and gravy.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° until potatoes are tender.

title: beef goulash
directions: Brown beef
in oil in pot.
Stir in dry onion soup mix, tomato paste
and
water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 2 hours. Cook sliced carrots in microwave for 15 minutes.
Pour carrots and carrot juice into beef mixture.
Continue simmering.
Cook noodles according
to
directions.
Serve
in
separate bowl. Pour goulash in bowl to be spooned over noodles at the table.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Fry meatballs until brown.
Place the meatballs in a large pot; cover the meatballs with water and add a few bouillon cubes.
Cover.
Over low heat, cook approximately 1 hour.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until apples are done and toothpick comes out clean.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Stir in a little flour if potatoes are watery.
Shape into cakes and fry in a well-greased skillet.
Or fry in deep fat, turning once.
Delicious served with applesauce as a topping.

title: hot lima casserole
directions: Cook limas as
directed
on
package. Cook soup, cheese and pepper until
cheese
melts.
Add
butter;	put beans into greased casserole. Add soup mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: In small amount of oil, stir-fry onion, garlic and zucchini about 3 minutes. Add seasonings. Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until just tender.
Add tomatoes and bay leaves.
Cover and cook over moderate heat 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add flour to thicken and more salt, if required. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serve it cold or hot as a meat accompaniment. Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple pineapple salad
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients and cook until thickened over low heat.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add 4 peeled, diced apples.
Mix with pineapple mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Then add sifted flour alternately with milk, beginning with flour and ending with flour. Bake in large greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Brown onion in hot fat. Stir in flour, then stir in rest of ingredients. Add about 1/2 cup tomato juice (drained from tomatoes) to make a sauce of medium thickness. Let simmer until thickened.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Into large bowl, measure flour, butter, sugar, orange juice and egg yolk.
With mixer on medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°. Use part of dough at a time.
Keep rest covered and refrigerated. Shape dough into balls.
Press deep thumb indentation.
Bake on cookie sheet, about 10 minutes, 5 minutes into baking, pull sheet out and repress down thumbprint.
Bake for rest of 5 minutes.
Take out and fill with a small bit of jam.
Place back in oven for 3 more minutes.
Remove to rack and cool.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, saute beef cubes in oil until dark brown.
Add water, soy sauce, 3 cups cabbage, onion, bacon, garlic, salt, pepper, mustard, potatoes (both kinds) and ketchup.
Cover and cook on low heat, 6 to 8 hours.
Before serving, heat again on high heat.
Add the 1 cup of cabbage left. Serve.

title: aunt essie's cobbler
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, mixing well with a large spoon.
Batter will be medium stiff.
Mix the fruit with sugar and 1 cup fruit juice.
Put fruit mixture in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Pour batter over fruit. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 325° and bake 15 to 30 minutes more until, when tested, there is no soft dough.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In
a
large bowl, mix all items except cucumbers.
Add cucumbers and mix.	Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: sour cream and berry pie
directions: Combine crumbs, nuts, flour and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir in melted butter; toss.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: clam cheese dunk
directions: Mash cheese.
Drain clams; save juice.
Add clams, Tabasco, garlic, onion and lemon juice to cheese; add enough clam juice for dunking consistency.
Serve with chips.
Yields 2 to 2 1/2 cups.

title: burger beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marshmal-o-fudge
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, butter, Marshmallow Creme and evaporated milk.
When totally boiling all over, time 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips. Stir until starts to thicken up.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: spoon cornbread
directions: Gradually stir the corn meal into the milk.
Let it come to a boil until it becomes mush.
Add salt, butter, eggs and baking powder.
Put mixture in round souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: reuben, reuben dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: In a small saucepan, combine corned beef, Swiss cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and sauerkraut.
Cook over low heat to combine ingredients as cheese melts.
Thin with milk to dipping consistency.
Serve warm with rye crackers or bread sticks.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups buttermilk with the meal.
Add well beaten eggs and salt.
Dissolve soda in the remaining buttermilk and stir into batter.
Pour into greased baking dish and add shortening.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-green bean bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken, green beans, vegetables, chopped onion and cheese.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with French fried onions and bake 10 minutes or longer, until onions are brown.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Dump all together and beat well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: roo's favorite rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; set aside.
Beat egg. Add sugar, 1 cup warm water and oil.
Mix in flour to liquid ingredients.
Add yeast.
Mix well.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and blend with mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish mustard.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Chop egg whites and combine with bacon, onion, potatoes and salad dressing.
Fold in mayonnaise mixture and season to taste with salt and celery seed.

title: ginger ale congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Let cool. Add ginger ale.
Stir well. Put in refrigerator until it starts to set. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in mold and chill until firm.

title: sausage balls(about 4 dozen)
directions: Mix well; form into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen, unbaked, for future use.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in bottom of pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with marshmallow cream.
Add coloring; mix until smooth.
Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: ground beef n tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon potato mixture in a rounded ring around top outer edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggs a'la texas
directions: Chop beef very fine.
Melt butter.
Add all ingredients, except eggs.
Heat and then add eggs.
Cook like scrambled eggs. Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the bacon on top and put in oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and brown slightly.
Add brown sugar and flour and stir until blended.
Add milk and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over direct heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked shell and top with meringue.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Mix cheeses and set aside.
Cook ground beef.
Drain grease and add chili and enchilada sauce.
Let cook 5 minutes. Butter tops of each tortilla. Wrap in plastic wrap and microwave until real warm (1 to 2 minutes).
Fill tortillas. Add cheese, roll and place, fold side down, in long casserole dish.
Pour leftover mixture on top. Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Add more cheese on top and let melt.

title: "corny" cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until top is slightly brown.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine all cans of fruit in baking dish. Combine brown sugar, butter, and curry stirring well. Spoon over fruit. Cover and bake till thoroughly heated. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Bring the vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and cool.
Shred cabbage (4 to 5 cups) and carrot.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out all liquid.
Cover with vinegar solution and freeze.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift into large bowl, the flour, cut in shortening; add buttermilk and yeast which has been dissolved in water.
Stir until moist, knead a few minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased pan and let raise 1 hour, brush with milk and butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in three-quart saucepan.
Boil two minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: veronica perry's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and spices together.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add to mixture.
Add 1 cup milk, butter and vanilla. Beat egg whites (not too dry).
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Put in shell and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and continue baking until knife in center comes out clean.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then butter and beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold in last.
Bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Put the dough through a cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet or roll into small balls and press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: In
large
heavy
pan
brown ground beef with onion and parsley; add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Meanwhile,
cook
lasagna
noodles
as
directed
on package.
Mix
eggs and cottage cheese together.
Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and an
x
8-inch
pan, spread about 1/2 cup meat sauce in each.
Alternate
layers of lasagna, meat sauce, cottage cheese mixture
and
Mozzarella
cheese until pans are full. Sprinkle generously
with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Great warmed up.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in bag.
Shake chicken in bag with this mix.

title: marinade
directions: This may be used with 2 1/2 to 3 pounds chicken, pork chops and steak.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: bewitching brew
directions: Combine solid ingredients; add water and mix well.
Heat thoroughly.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 40 minutes, covered, at 325°.
Then, remove cover and brown.

title: hawkins family brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken until meat separates from bone.
Remove bones; cut meat into bite size pieces.
Reserve all chicken stock.
After stock has cooled, skim some grease off top.
Cook pork roast; break apart meat.
Add chicken and pork to stock; heat through. Add tomatoes, puree and add water as necessary.
Add potatoes, onions, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Add lima beans and whole corn.
Add creamed corn last. Add more water and tomato sauce to taste.

title: hurry up pie
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 8-inch pan in moderate oven.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour mixture into melted margarine.
Stir lightly.
Into this pour 1 quart of fruit (peaches, apples, apricots or berries, juice and all).
Distribute evenly, then bake at 350° until crust forms on top and browns, about 30 minutes.
Spoon or cut out.
Serve with table cream, ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Best served warm.

title: cheese roast
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in a 7 x 11-inch flat Pyrex casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with jellied cranberry sauce.

title: au gratin potatoes and ham
directions: In slow cooker, layer 1/2 of potatoes, ham, onion and cheese. Repeat layers.
In a small bowl, combine soup, milk and thyme; pour over top.
Cover; cook on high setting for 3 hours.
Reduce to low setting; cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: winter squash, apple and walnut soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except the walnuts to be used for garnish in a large saucepan and stir to blend well.
Cook the soup over medium heat until warmed through (15 minutes).
Ladle the soup into bowls and add a few chopped walnut pieces in the center. Makes 6 servings.
Quick and delicious!

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar and baking powder, not too stiff. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased Pyrex pie pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pickled pineapple
directions: Place
pineapple
chunks
in jar with lid.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan and simmer 10 to 12 minutes. Pour
hot
mixture
over
pineapple.
Seal jar.
Refrigerate a minimum of 3 to 4 days.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine soups, chilies, spices, Tabasco sauce and 1 cup broth. Mix well.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 cups corn chips.
Spread 1/2 of chicken over this, then half of sauce mix and half of the grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Put in a greased casserole dish (8 x 8-inch) the zucchini, tomato and onion.
Mix with an electric mixer the milk, eggs, Parmesan cheese and Bisquick.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple.
Use juice and enough water to make 1 cup.
Add juice to dissolve Jell-O, total of 3 cups of liquid only.
Mix other ingredients and fold into Jell-O.
Top with sliced peach or cherry in a dab of Cool Whip after refrigerated.

title: spider cookies
directions: Spread the peanut butter onto a vanilla wafer, then place another wafer on top.
Roll the wafer in the coconut so that the coconut sticks to the peanut butter, then make the eyes and mouth with the icing.

title: capoosta
directions: Place all ingredients except rice in a large saucepan.
Cook for 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Add rice to mixture and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Next mix together buttermilk, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures then gradually add flour until well mixed.
Grease cookie sheet well.
Bake at 425°.
This batter is very soupy.
Makes very moist cookies.

title: linda aquilina's eileen rocks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets lightly with margarine.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Work softened butter in bowl until creamy.
Add sugar and blend well. Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with bourbon.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in raisins. Drop by teaspoon of dough 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Cool on a cookie sheet and then place on a wire rack to cool.

title: chili nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Spread chili over this.
Spread cheese on top of this.
Shredded Cheddar may also be added at this time.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: mississippi potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes with mayo, salt, pepper, diced cheese and onion. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: graham cracker munchies
directions: Break crackers into small pieces and arrange on a foil-lined cookie sheet. Turn the foil up around the edges. Boil the butter, margarine and sugar together for 3 minutes. Pour over the crackers and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: trophy winning strawberry cake
directions: Put mix in bowl and add other ingredients.
Beat in mixer 4 minutes.
Bake in layers as directed on mix box.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake one hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: lite punch bowl cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Crumble cake in a punch bowl or other suitable dish.
Beat pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Allow to thicken about 5 minutes.
Pour on top of crumbled cake.
Slice strawberries, sprinkle with Equal and allow to set until strawberries form their own juice.
Place on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip, 1/16 of cake is 222 calories.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix egg, salmon and salt in bowl; add enough corn meal to make a stiff batter.
Pinch off.
Roll into ball and flatten (pat flat in hand).
Fry in frypan on medium-high heat.
Turn once; drain on paper towel.
Good served with dry peas or beans.

title: nonnie's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients and add together.
Blended best by using fingers. Take 1/2 cup crumbs out for topping.
Add sour milk and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese and ham dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill before serving.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: pearlie's cheese cake
directions: Moisten cornstarch with a little cream; blend cottage cheese in food processor.
Add eggs one at a time, sugar, lemon rind, cornstarch and vanilla.
Last, mix in cream.
Bake at 300° until done in center, about 1 hour.

title: unfried fish fillets
directions: Spray baking sheet to coat.
Combine cornmeal, thyme, basil and Old Bay seasoning on large platter.
Dip each fillet into until coated on both sides.
Place on baking sheet and spray lightly with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake another 5 minutes until golden and fish flakes easily.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Spread in 8 to 9-inch dish.
Top with tomatoes, Cheddar cheese and sliced black olives.

title: sinful stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slice off top of bread and hollow out inside of bread.
Pour mixture inside of hollowed out bread.
Put top back on bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may use pieces of bread for dippers or use crackers, chips, etc.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and let stand overnight.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, nuts, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until sugar is dissolved, then add Cool Whip and mix until well blended.
Spread over cooled pretzel layer.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool and thicken slightly.
Add strawberries and spread over cream cheese layer. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots, then dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 layer pans at 325° for 40 minutes or bake 55 minutes for loaf pan.

title: eggplant dish
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices. Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender. Drain well.

title: punch for weddings
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with strawberries.
Good with cake. It isn't too sweet.

title: easy beet pickles
directions: Drain the juice from the can of beets; save 3/4 cup of juice and mix with the sugar, vinegar and salt. Extra sugar and/or vinegar may be added if you want it more sweet or sour. Put the beets in container and add the liquid. This should set for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: good and easy spanish beans
directions: Start with big pan.
You can use black beans, red beans or pinto beans. (Wash the beans well if from a can.)

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, butter, 1 egg, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and 1 teaspoon vanilla; blend well.
Turn into prepared pan and sprinkle with blueberries.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer of graham crackers.
Mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture on layer of graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers in pan.
Top with remaining half of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Mix frosting with 3 teaspoons milk for spreading consistency.
Spread frosting over top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: While hot, mix spaghetti, egg, butter and Parmesan cheese. Pour into a 10-inch pie plate and form a crust.
Spread Ricotta cheese on pie crust.
Brown ground beef in a skillet and pour onto Ricotta cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the pie and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove pie and add Mozzarella cheese.
Cook a remaining 5 to 15 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Add extra spaghetti sauce as desired.

title: pat's pie
directions: Gently fold all ingredients in with egg whites.
Press into a greased 8-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: special k candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and butter; bring to boil in large pan. Add peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Add cereal.
Pack into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate and butterscotch chips melted together.
Spread over mix in pan.
Let cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: fresh orange cheesecake
directions: Beat egg well in large bowl.
Add the cream cheese and beat again.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add sour cream and orange juice.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Turn off oven and let stand in oven for 1 hour.
Remove and let cool.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Put beets into small serving dish.
In small saucepan, combine beet liquid and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over beets.
Refrigerate until well chilled, about 1 hour.

title: coffee shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender container. Cover.
Process at high speed until foamy.
Yields 1 serving.

title: sugarless health cookies
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 3 minutes.
Add shortening and cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced cabbage-sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 3-inch lengths on the diagonal.
In a large, heavy frying pan, heat butter.
Add onions, cabbage, chicken broth and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients along with sausage.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender and sausage is piping hot.
Makes about 4 servings.
Very good!

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Make pudding according to directions and set aside.
Mix flour, salt, margarine and half of the nuts.
Press into bottom of square pan and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and half of whipped topping.
After crust has cooled, spread this mixture on it.
Top evenly with pudding and then top pudding with remainder of whipped topping.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Refrigerate until served.
You may double this recipe and use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Melt
oleo
and saute onion, pepper and pimentos slowly 10 minutes.
Add broth,
soup,
chicken,
cut	in
bite
size pieces, and cheese.
Pour in casserole and bake in a 350° oven until hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove bones.
Put noodles in broth and bring to a boil.
Combine soups in a saucepan; heat and stir until well combined.
Add sour cream.
In large pan, pour chicken, soups and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over mixture and add butter.
Heat until brown and bubbling.

title: chewy cakes
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs together with mixer. Add flour and vanilla. Stir in nuts by hand. Pour into a 13 x 19 inch baking pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well with portable mixer.
Put in casserole.

title: hot chocolate float
directions: Fix hot chocolate as directed.
Add whipped cream.
Don't stir.
Add a cherry and a little juice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Using medium-sized bowl and mixer at medium speed, mix about 8 minutes. Pour filling in pie shell and put pecan halves on top.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Make tea and while still warm stir and dissolve sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients and warm on low heat for at least 30 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: lone star steak marinade
directions: Grate peppers, with or without seeds, and blend liquids together.
Pour over steak in marinating bowl.
Soak for 1/2 hour to 6 hours, depending on thickness of steak.
Cook as usual.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cream last.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can be eaten hot or refrigerated for several days and eaten cold.

title: peach slush with blueberries
directions: Arrange peaches in a single layer in a jelly roll pan (or any flat pan) and freeze for 30 to 45 minutes.
When frozen, put in a food processor with the sugar, water, lemon juice and vanilla and process until slushy.
Add the sour cream with the machine running and process until smooth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add to broccoli in pan 1/2 stick margarine in chunks and the cheese in chunks.
Stir until melted. Put into casserole.
Crush crackers; put these on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a 9-inch pan. Serves 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with vegetable oil spray.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish, arrange by layer the first 6 ingredients.
Repeat layers until dish is filled.
Put Parmesan cheese on top layer.
Fill dish half way with milk.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400° or until brown.

title: oyster cracker surprise
directions: Put 3 large grocery bags inside each other to absorb oil.
Put crackers and all dry ingredients in sacks and shake.
Add 1 cup oil, a little at a time, shaking as you go.
Whenever you think of it during the day, shake sack several times.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Buy ready made pie crusts.
(They are folded in a box, 2 crusts to a box.)
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with the crust.
Put butter in a skillet and saut onion and celery until vegetables are soft.
You can also saut the mixed vegetables a little before adding them.
Boil your chicken breasts and cut them up into small pieces.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Spray baking dish or loaf pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs and add all ingredients, leaving Grape-Nuts until last. Pour into baking dish or loaf pan and place in a pan of hot water.
Place both pans in the oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu(microwave)
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half. Pound between Saran Wrap to 1/4 inch cutlets.
Place a slice of cheese and a slice of ham on each chicken cutlet.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Brown in a skillet.
Combine soup and milk and pour into a microwave-safe dish.
Arrange chicken rolls on top.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Rearrange rolls and cook 6 minutes more.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: italian pretzels
directions: Spread pretzels on jelly roll pan.
Combine oil, dressing mix, dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic powder in bowl; mix well.
Pour over pretzels.
Stir well.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with onion bits and add crisp bacon, crumbled.
In large bowl, break up lettuce.
Cut up tomatoes, half or whole green pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Add meat mixture and beans.
Just before serving, toss with Western salad dressing and serve with nacho cheese chips.
The chips may be crumbled or eaten with the salad.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts and sprinkle in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and pecans.
Heat 8 ounces softened cream cheese and stick of margarine in saucepan.
Thoroughly mix, then add the powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, butter, chocolate and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add nuts. Spread into 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool well on wire rack. Cut into squares.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar or frost.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender. Blend until thick and foamy.
Add artificial sweetener if desired.

title: crab dip
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and add to mayo in large bowl. Stir in onions, eggs, crab meat and shrimp.
Mix well.
Best if chilled overnight.
Serve as a dip on club crackers.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix in flour and salt.
Fold in chips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: mom's cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Add sugar and melted butter and mix well.
Pat crust into 9-inch square pan and set aside.

title: sassy zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1-inch strips.
Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Mix in tomatoes, water and sauce mix and bring to a boil. Stir in rice and zucchini.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bread twists
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Let set about 5 minutes until foamy.
Beat in salt, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough out on flour-covered surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Roll dough into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough and divide into 8 equal pieces.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple including syrup in saucepan and heat on stove until Jell-O melts.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add buttermilk and Cool Whip, one at a time, mixing thoroughly, then add pecans.
Pour into serving dish or mold.
Chill several hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients, cornstarch, sugar and salt. Put milk to simmer in 2-quart pot.
Take egg yolks and add some warm milk to them and mix to dry ingredients.
Add to pot and cook until thickened.
Add coconut; stir constantly.
Add to pie crust. Beat egg whites for meringue; put on top of pies and bake until golden brown.

title: big bay strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to boil gently.
Add cornstarch and 1/2 cup water, mixed.
Cook until clear and thick, about 5 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O.
Cool a little.
Fold in strawberries into baked shell.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet dill chips
directions: Cut the pickles into chunks or slices.
Put the sugar and pickles in the original jar and refrigerate for about 6 days. Pickles will be very crispy. Will keep a long time.

title: unbelievable pinto bean pie
directions: Mash pinto beans and juice into a paste.
Mix all ingredients except nuts.
When mixed well, add nuts. Stir well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until top browns.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and ice just before serving.
Add red food coloring (a few drops) if desired.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground meat with 1/2 onion. Precook potatoes (5 minutes in microwave or boil until slightly tender). Add potatoes and remaining ingredients to meat. Simmer until potatoes are tender. Salt and pepper to taste. Quick and easy. Good served with corn bread.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften so it will be easier to blend. Blend cream cheese and Old English spread together until smooth. Add shrimp and mix well. Add ground celery seed and Tabasco sauce and mix well.

title: apple sweet potato casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Add apples; layer with marshmallows.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle over marshmallows.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water until smooth; pour over all.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
May make several days ahead;
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; add beans, rice and spaghetti.
Grate cheese and put on top.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Make sure everything is hot through and through.

title: bread pudding #1
directions: Spread toasted bread with margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into pieces.
Butter baking dish. Sprinkle with raisins.
Top with bread pieces.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Take biscuits and roll each between hands until forms a long piece of dough.
Take fork and stir each piece of dough in butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mixture until completely covered and then tie each in a knot.
Place in baking dish and bake 8 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken and artichoke salad
directions: Mix juice of artichokes with 1/4 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 teaspoon curry.

title: almond sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, mixing as you go.
Add almond extract.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Carefully fold into other mixture.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured at 300° for an hour and a half.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and margarine. Add 6 cups water, bouillon cubes, boil until dissolved, add noodles and broccoli.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese.
Stir constantly until melted.
Add milk (as much as 6 cups) to thin.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order listed in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread over cheese layer. Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Chill.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Parboil chicken, bone, skin and cut in pieces.
Put in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish. Mix mushrooms, soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing according to package and put on top.
Dot with butter and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: red hots cinnamon salad
directions: Melt the candies in hot water before dissolving the gelatin. Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: harvest fruit pie
directions: Mix together and put in the pie crust.
Top with butter and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour into oiled bread loaf pans and bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add zucchini and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nuts.
Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves baked at 350°.

title: ham tater tots
directions: Bake at 500° for 30 minutes.
Eat.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt butter; mix flour and nuts in pie pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown; cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides, then tear up and put into an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat your eggs and milk together and pour over your bread.
Brown your meat and spread over the top of your casserole.
Spread your grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and enjoy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Butter either an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a 4-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and peanuts until completely coated. Fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture in pan using buttered back of spoon.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Refrigerate any remaining squares.
Yields 25 squares.

title: crystallized mint leaves
directions: Beat egg white in saucer until spreadable.
A few drops of water may be added if needed.
Using a small paint brush, cover every surface of a leaf with egg white in as thin as possible a layer.
Tweezers will help to hold them.
As you coat each leaf, lay it on the sugar and sprinkle more sugar over it until evenly coated.
Lay on cake rack that has been covered with wax paper. Set rack in warm, dry place (oven heated pilot light) and dry for several days.
Store in layers between waxed paper.
Keep dry.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese; mix with hands.
Add Bisquick, a small amount at a time.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Place in baking dish; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in next five ingredients. Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: slim jim nicole salad
directions: Mix together potatoes, beans, onions and olives.
Pour dressing over this.
Cover and chill a couple of hours in refrigerator. Combine these vegetables with tuna and greens.
Toss lightly. Garnish with egg slices and serve.

title: pita pinwheels
directions: Mix minced leeks in cream cheese.
Spread on pita.
Top with meat, then lettuce.
Roll up tight, then wrap in plastic wrap. Put in fridge overnight.
Eat whole or slice into pinwheels for snacks.

title: my favorite casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, celery and green pepper. Combine soup, milk, salt and cooked rice in a saucepan.
Cook until well mixed. Remove from heat and add cheese, stirring well.
Combine with hamburger and put into casserole dish, topping with bread crumbs if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Serve with taco chips.

title: rice salad(hot or cold)
directions: Cook Rice-a-Roni according to package directions and let cool.
Add all remaining ingredients to rice mixture with the mayonnaise (using only enough to make it stick together).
Pepper to taste.

title: delicious frozen fruit salad
directions: Prepare gelatin.
Add fruits, salt, sugar and lemon juice; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
When it begins to thicken, fold in whipped cream and macaroons.
Put back in icebox.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Slice French bread into 1-inch thick slices; spread cheese mixture on slices.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until bubbly and crusty.

title: microwave cheese broccoli-stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, egg, 1/4 cup of bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons of onions, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, basil and pepper in medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Set aside.

title: marcy's potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Boil potatoes with skin on and cut into chunks.
Cube Velveeta.
Mix all in a large bowl with mayonnaise.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spam quiche
directions: Saute Spam, onion and green pepper in oil until vegetables are tender.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender or with hand mixer until smooth.
Pour evenly into pie plate.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream together.
Drain 1 to 2 1/2 pounds canned yams and mash up.
Mix together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside: flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream shortening and gradually add sugars.
Add eggs and beat well until light and fluffy.
Add flour.
Mix in oats, vanilla and chocolate pieces.
(This dough will be crumbly.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
If you make your cookies small enough, this recipe should make about 11 dozen.

title: breakfast fried rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
(Roll sausage in a few paper towels for more removal of grease, if desired.) Return sausage to skillet and add carrots, celery, onion and pressed garlic.
Simmer in covered skillet until desired tenderness.
Add eggs and rice.
Season as desired.
Good with hot sauce.
Use your favorite veggies.

title: sausage stars
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Mix sausage, cheese and Ranch dressing. Cut wonton wrappers in 1/4. Place wrapper in cupcake pan. Brush with oil. Bake empty at 350° for approximately 5 minutes or until brown. Remove from oven. Fill shells with mixture. Place back in oven at 350°. Bake until bubbly. Serve hot.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Use can condensed milk to thin Miracle Whip, about 3/4 can. Mix with sugar, vinegar, salt, chopped onion, cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces. Pour Miracle Whip dressing over vegetables.
Chill.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Blend and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Make a sauce
by
combining
soups, tomatoes and broth. Cut tortillas into quarters and
layer in a large dish tortillas, chicken, onions and
cheese.
Pour	1/4 sauce over layers and repeat until all layers
are
used.
End
with
a layer of cheese. Cover and cook 30	minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook 30 minutes more.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Add Lawry's sauce mix, V-8 juice, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Put small amount of oil in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Put meat sauce on bottom, then noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let sit 15 minutes before cutting.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Combine in blender until well mixed.
Makes 1 egg.
Keeps up to 1 week in refrigerator.
May be frozen.
This recipe can be multiplied several times to make several eggs at a time.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine sugar and Miracle Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except olives and bacon. Place in 9 x 13 inch baking casserole dish. Top with bacon and olives. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 12. This is a great dish to take to a potluck or for a crowd. It can also easily be halved for a smaller group.

title: spaghetti with broccoli(or peas)
directions: Wash broccoli (or peas).
Cook broccoli in salted water (do not overcook; try to keep it firm).
Save the cooking water from the broccoli.
(If using peas, you do not have to precook.)
Saute in olive oil the garlic, salt and pepper until brown.
Add cooked broccoli (or peas) to browned garlic.
Add saved cooking water (or add water if using peas) just to cover.
Cook until just boiling (or until peas are cooked).
Prepare spaghetti per directions. Once cooked, drain (save about 1 cup water from spaghetti) and toss broccoli (peas) over spaghetti.
If not enough liquid, add more water (from spaghetti).
Toss with grated cheese.

title: granny's brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in chocolate syrup and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Beat in flour a little at a time.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Granny's Brownie Icing.

title: apple tapioca pudding
directions: Slice apples into rings 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick; place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and cinnamon; dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven while preparing pudding.

title: stuffed hot peppers
directions: Clean hot peppers and cut off ends.
Stuff with sauerkraut and stand up in quart jars.
Bring brine to a boil.
Keep brine boiling hot.
Cover the peppers and seal jars.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Put chicken, salt, pepper, paprika and green pepper in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, blend onion soup mix and cornstarch.
Stir in 3/4 cup pineapple juice and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil, over medium heat, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Stir in lemon juice, brown sugar, soy sauce, ginger and rosemary.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add pineapple, pushing pieces down in sauce.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes, basting a couple of times, until tender.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in fruit and whipped topping.
Add nuts.
Freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Handy to have in the freezer. Kids and adults love it!

title: cream pralines
directions: Mix sugar, pecans and milk in heavy saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (238°). Cool slightly and beat with spoon until mix begins to thicken.

title: mulled wine
directions: Slice lemon and combine with sugar, water and spices.
Heat to boiling and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Turn heat to low; add wine and heat very hot, but do not boil.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in bottle and shake.

title: peanut butter yummies
directions: Heat corn syrup and confectioners sugar and vanilla in saucepan.
Add peanut butter until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spoon on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 5 minutes.

title: butterfinger cheesecake
directions: Mix crust to box directions; set aside.

While candy bar is still in wrapper, beat with a large spoon to crumble. Mix cheesecake to box directions. Stir in 3/4 of broken candy bar pieces. Place cheesecake mixture in crust. Crumble remaining candy bar on top of cheesecake.
Chill and serve.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with a fork; add shortening and water. Let stand 20 minutes; heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with fork, add vanilla, sugar and flour, beating with fork.
Add date mixture, mixing to just blend.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender for two minutes on blend.
Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Chill.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Drain beets (if fresh, cook).
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt. Stir in undrained pineapple. Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add butter, lemon juice and beets.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is brown.
Add salt. Dip tortilla in hot oil; fry quickly until limp.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon equal amounts of meat mixture on tortillas.
Top each with taco sauce and cheese.
Roll up; place seam side down in lightly greased 6 x 10-inch pan.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and bouillon, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add water; cook, stirring in sour cream and chillies.
Pour mixture over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Make a graham cracker crust. Combine rhubarb, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until rhubarb is soft.
Pour over crust.
Cool.
Cover with 3 cups miniature marshmallows.
Cover with 2 cups Cool Whip.
Mix pudding, made according to package directions.
Spread on Cool Whip layer. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill until firm.

title: carol wood's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pour 1/4 cup oil in pan.
Put meat loaf in pan and cook on top of stove.

title: crunchy cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium size serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with turkey, chicken or pork.

title: veal paprika
directions: Thinly slice clove of garlic and brown lightly in butter.
Add veal and brown well.
Add 1 cup of water, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add sour cream, paprika and salt.
Blend well and cook slowly over low heat for 10 minutes longer.
Serve over buttered rice or wide noodles.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine.
Mix together.
Line bottom of pan with mix.
Save 1/4 cup mix for top of dessert.
Mix together milk, pudding and ice cream.
Pour into pan.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: gift toffee(chocolate and almond toffee)
directions: Lightly butter an 11 x 15-inch shallow baking pan and set aside.
Combine butter and sugar in a heavy pan (4-quart).
Cook over moderate heat, stirring hard with wooden spoon to blend butter and sugar, until mixture boils.
Then cover with a tight fitting lid and cook about 3 minutes more.
Remove lid and continue cooking, stirring occasionally if necessary to blend in butter, until temperature reaches 290° on a candy thermometer (about 6 minutes).
Pour immediately into buttered pan and set on a flat surface to cool.

title: so good potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of mixture with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour.

title: taco cheese dip(crock-pot)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Add remaining ingredients and put into a crock-pot. Heat 1 to 2 hours to blend the flavors. Keeps for several hours on low.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine, Karo and salt.
Cook and boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat and pour into buttered dish.

title: blueberry-date breakfast bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Blend eggs, yogurt and orange juice in mixing bowl.
Add date bread mix and stir in with fork.
Stir in blueberry muffin mix, adding the drained blueberries last.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Pour into pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Partially thaw broccoli.
Cook onions and celery in margarine in frypan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
(Use no water with soups.)
Place everything in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt, soda and flour well.
Add beaten eggs and fruit cocktail.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in pan over medium heat until brown; drain off grease.
Put ground beef, beans and other ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with desired toppings.
(Toppings such as: tortilla chips, shredded Monterey Jack cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes or sour cream.)

title: sausage and potato stew
directions: Bring sausage and 1/4 cup of the water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring once or twice, until water evaporates.
Reduce heat to low.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk with shortening and sugar.
Cool; add yeast and dissolve thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Place in large bowl; grease surface, cover and place in refrigerator.
Make rolls as wanted.
Keeps well for 1 week.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and softened oleo and then add sifted flour a little at a time and refrigerate overnight. When ready to make pinch off a small amount and place in a tart or small muffin pan and spread over the bottom and sides of each tart pan and fill with the following mixture.

title: roasted broccoli(delicious!)
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Separate broccoli into flowerets and cut off all stalk.
Put into large bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup olive oil over broccoli and toss until broccoli is lightly coated.
Place broccoli in cookie sheet.
Put in oven on top rack.
Watch closely!
Cook 5 minutes and check.
Edges should turn slightly brown when ready.
Remove and flip over flowerets and broil 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: broccoli puff pie(makes 6 servings, 9-inch pie dish)
directions: Place butter in custard cup.
Microwave on High until butter melts.
Stir warm butter into broccoli, to coat.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: In a very large
bowl,	mix
cereal
with sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and milk.	Mix well.
Store in a covered container in
the
refrigerator
and
use
as desired. Batter will keep for 6	weeks.	To bake, preheat oven to 400°. Fill greased muffin tins
two-thirds
full
and	bake 15 to 20 minutes.	Cool 10 minutes in
pan and turn out.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen muffins.

title: fish chowder, 1961
directions: Simmer fish in water for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving broth. Pick meat from bones and reserve; discard bones.
Saute onion, garlic and pepper in butter until onion is transparent.
Add reserved stock, tomatoes, potatoes, celery, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add reserved fish meat and parsley and reheat.

title: oven baked chicken 'n' rice
directions: Mix soups and rice together.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barley veggie soup
directions: Cook all in crock-pot overnight or in Dutch kettle for 3 hours. Brown chuck roast or stew meat.

title: cinnamon cucumbers
directions: Peel, slice and seed 2 gallons cucumbers.
Soak in lime and 8 1/2 cups water for 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Soak in clear water for 3 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar well.
Add egg, then applesauce.
Combine the dry ingredients; add to the egg mixture. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top before baking.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini about halfway; drain well.
Mix together melted butter, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook on top of stove on low heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and stir in onion.
Mix sauce and drained zucchini; put into baking dish and top with remaining melted butter, mixed into bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brown and drain sausage. Butter bread.
Line the pan with 4 slices of bread, cut in half and buttered side down.
Cover with sausage.
Add the cheese slices to cover the meat.
Add rest of the bread, halved and buttered side up.
Beat eggs well; add milk.
Pour over the bread. Leave in the refrigerator overnight.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until test done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pans before removing to wire racks to cool completely.
Frost with Lemon Orange Frosting.

title: texas chili
directions: Cook beans and drain, saving 1 cup liquid.
Cook meat until it loses its red color, breaking it with a fork.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add seasonings. Break up tomatoes, combine with meat, beans and 1 cup bean liquid. Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies *
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa, milk and salt in a saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add vanilla, peanut butter, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix well and drop on wax paper while warm.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Brown ground meat, drain.
Add onion and pepper, set aside.
Combine eggs, 1 cup corn and milk with cornbread mix.
Stir just till dry ingredients are moistened. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 inch square pan.
Top with beef mixture, cheese slices and remaining cup of corn.
Pour remaining 1/2 of batter on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: little pigs
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2 and mash flat.
Roll sausages up in biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and follow biscuit directions on can.

title: creamed crab meat and shrimp sauce
directions: Make white sauce with milk, flour and butter.
Then add cheese, green pepper, catsup, crab meat, shrimp and sherry.
Serve with Petits Choux.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (8 or 9-inch square); mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk and pour into the melted butter. Spread peeled and sliced fresh peaches over the mixture.
Sprinkle sugar over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Saute onions, pepper and rice in oil in skillet over high heat until lightly brown, stirring constantly.
Add hot water and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions and celery in shortening and margarine in electric skillet.
Layer remaining ingredients on top.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring gently several times.
Cheese should stay on top.

title: yellow squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain off water and mash until fine.
Add salt, pepper, cheese, butter, egg yolks and crackers, crumbled fine.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in buttered casserole dish until brown.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Peel and grate raw sweet potatoes, then grate the lemon.
Beat eggs and sugar together and stir into potato mixture.
Add spices, salt, molasses, milk and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 hour in iron skillet that has been buttered.

title: applesauce tea bread
directions: Combine flour, Sweetness and Light, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add flour mixture all at once, stirring just until flour is dampened; spoon into lightly greased 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into roll.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice in the morning and bake at 325° to 350° about 10 minutes.

title: pepper chicken fettucini toss
directions: Heat oil.
Add chicken, peppers, onion, mushrooms and garlic. Cook and stir over medium heat until chicken is cooked, 8 to 12 minutes, or until vegetables are done.
Serve over fettucini.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix the parsley, onion and cheese together in a small bowl. Layer 1/3 of the cubed bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Place half of the parsley-onion-cheese mixture on first layer.
Repeat with 1/3 of the bread, other half of parsley mixture and top with remaining 1/3 cubed bread.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over bread/cheese mixture.
Sliver margarine over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
I usually leave it covered for about 25 minutes, then uncover it so it can brown nicely.

title: tunaburgers
directions: Combine ingredients and fill buns with mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: marinade of venison or beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate meat overnight.
Roast meat, but save marinade.
Heat separately to use as sauce or thicken to use as gravy.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In large bowl combine Chex, sugar, salt and shortening.
Heat milk and 1 1/4 cups water to boiling.
Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Cool to warm.
Stir frequently.
Dissolve yeast in remaining 1/4 cup water.
Stir into cereal mixture. Add 2 cups flour. Mix well. Stir in enough additional flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Work in additional flour as needed.
Form into ball. Put into greased bowl.
Turn to grease all sides.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place, free from draft, until double, about 1 hour. Punch dough down.
Place on lightly floured surface.
Knead about 2 minutes.
Form into two loaves.
Place in two greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Brush tops of loaves with melted butter.
Let rise in warm place until almost double, about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread sounds hollow when lightly tapped.
Remove from pans at once. Cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli corn scallop
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Blend in flour. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in corn and 1/4 cup crumbs.
Arrange broccoli in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Combine 7-Up and ginger ale.
Add sherbet; stir until sherbet is partially melted.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and butter. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix well. Roll into little balls then roll balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brown soup stock
directions: Cut the lean meat from the bones and brown 1/3 of it in the marrow taken from the bones. Put the rest of the meat and bones in a large kettle and cover with the water and let stand for 1 hour. Add the browned meat and seasonings and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and cook slowly for 5 hours, removing scum as it forms on top. Add the vegetables and cook 1 1/2 hours longer. Strain through a cheesecloth and cool.

title: taco dogs
directions: Prepare hot dogs according to package directions.
Place a cheese slice and hot dog in each taco shell; top with beans. Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry(china)
directions: In a small bowl blend 6 Tbsp. of water, soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar. In a large skillet, over high heat, cook chicken and ginger in 1 Tbsp. of oil. Cook until chicken is lightly browned and cooked through. Remove and place on platter. Add remaining 1 Tbsp. oil to skillet, add vegetables and cook, stirring until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Return chicken to skillet with soy sauce mixture. Cook until sauce thickens and chicken is heated through.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper. Chill until set.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple crunch bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Reserve 2 cups flour mixture and set aside.
Add baking soda and next 3 ingredients to remaining flour mixture; beat well.
Add vanilla and next 2 ingredients; beat well.
Stir in apple.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Stir in onions.
Cook, covered, over medium heat until done.
Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce; and if you want, a dash of pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Shred lettuce; place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle peas over salad.
Spoon mayo evenly over the top of salad.
Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan and garlic powder.
Cover and chill in refrigerator as long as 24 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix eggs, molasses, sugar and oil.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons soda in 2 teaspoons hot water.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Add spices.
Add flour and beat well.
Add boiling water a little at a time, beating lightly.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish at 300° for 50 minutes or until done.
Check with toothpick.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: country chicken chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boil.
Serve topped with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: In covered wok or electric frypan, steam broccoli and cauliflower for 5 minutes.
Pour off water.
Add carrots, onion and sesame oil; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add zucchini and mushrooms, stirring constantly.
Add pea pods; fry 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle soy sauce over vegetables.

title: peach fluff
directions: Step 1: Mix and press into a 9 x 13 pan the flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger beef stroganoff
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef.
Add salt, pepper, onion and garlic.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and water.
Add to meat mixture.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: angel food delight
directions: Fold whipped topping into chocolate sauce just until blended. Split cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place one layer on a serving plate. Spread with 1/4 of the topping mixture and 1/4 of the toffee bits. Repeat layers. Top with remaining cake layer. Frost the top and sides with remaining topping mixture. Sprinkle with remaining toffee bits. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours. Store in the refrigerator. YIELD: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, break cranberry sauce up with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until smooth and blended.
Good on grill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain all but a little fat.
Mix in all ingredients, except cheese and Tater Tots.
Cook for 10 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese and then Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "strasbourg" wurst salad
directions: Combine the salt, sugar and vinegar; pour in the oil and whisk vigorously to make a smooth dressing.
Add the bologna and cheese, plus the onion and let stand for at least 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with the ground pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing and salad
directions: Pour dressing over the salad.

title: vegetable couscous pilaf
directions: Melt butter; add onion, zucchini, salt, pepper, garlic and basil.
Cook until zucchini is tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add wine; bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Stir in couscous, olives and tomatoes.
Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand until liquid is absorbed (about 5 minutes).
Before serving, fluff with fork; sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken rotini cacciatore
directions: In shallow bowl, combine flour and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Add simmered sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Add uncooked rotini, carrots and celery.
Cook uncovered an additional 8 to 12 minutes or until rotini and vegetables are tender, stirring frequently. Add zucchini and cook an additional 5 minutes or until tender. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: In one bowl mix jello with boiling water and set in refrigerator until kind of like jelly.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Cream real good.
Roll out graham crackers.
Mix with melted butter or oleo (enough for crust).
Put in bottom of pan.
Whip Milnot until real stiff.
Mix the two mixtures.
Be sure to mix in largest bowl.
Fold in whipped cream (real easy).
Pour into graham cracker pie mix.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs (plain) over top and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Cream bananas until fluffy. Mix dry ingredients together. Add bananas and dry mixture alternately to sugar mixture. Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "chicken corn chowder"(serves 4)
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in soup mix. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in corn and milk.
Heat through, but do not boil.

title: creative salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add pineapple and second fruit, drained.
Mix in nuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Allow to marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: pastry shells
directions: Mix above ingredients well. Shape into small balls & press in small cup cake pans. Bake at 300 degrees until golden brown.

title: cajun red beans and rice salad
directions: In small jar with tight fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, chili powder, seasoned salt, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Shake well.
Pour over rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Mix gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Serves 12.

title: cabbage-spinach
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add cloves of minced garlic and cabbage.
Place a tight fitting lid on sauce pan and allow cabbage to steam about 15 minutes.
Add spinach and return lid to pan. Cook until spinach is heated and cabbage is crisp tender.

title: broccoli-cheese noodle soup
directions: In a large pot, heat oil.
Add onions and saute over medium heat for 3 minutes.

Add water and bouillon cubes; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally until cubes are dissolved. Gradually add noodles and salt so that mixture continues to boil. Cook uncovered for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in celery, chicken, broccoli and garlic powder. Cook 4 minutes more. Add milk, cubed cheese and pepper and continue cooking on lower heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Eat and enjoy.

title: barbecued chicken deluxe
directions: Grill chicken breasts until done.
Saute white onion in butter and garlic salt.
Place grilled chicken in a glass cooking dish. Cover with barbecue sauce.
Sprinkle sauteed onions over sauce. Cover with cheese; place in oven until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and green onions.
Top with a scoop of sour cream and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in buttered casserole. Add mushroom soup.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven until thoroughly heated.

title: cindy's midwest egg casserole(assemble and refrigerate overnight)
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms at 5 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch glass Pyrex pan with margarine.
Spread 1 cup cheese.
Break the eggs over the cheese.
Break the yolks, but do not stir. Salt and pepper to taste (if you are used to low salt tastes, leave out the salt altogether, the ham is salted).
Spread on ham and mushrooms. Pour cream over all.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Place cold, in preheated oven. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy, delicious fruit cobbler
directions: Spread 1/2 box of dry cake mix in a 9 X 12-inch pan.
Spread in canned pie filling.
Spread the rest of the cake mix on top.
Pour water slowly over top.
Bake 50 - 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour and ice cream to form a batter.
Pour into lightly greased muffin cups.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: "impressive" chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti; drain and set aside.
Mix soup and sour cream. Combine half of soup mixture with chicken; mix well.
Reserve remaining soup mixture.
Stuff shells with chicken mixture; place in a greased dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender; set aside.
Combine water and bouillon until dissolved. Add to reserved soup mixture.
Stir soup mixture into mushroom mixture.
Spoon over manicotti; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: continental chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour until smooth.
Over low heat, slowly blend in broth, then cream.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Combine all seasonings, then blend into sauce.
Stir in wine; fold in eggs and chicken. Turn into buttered 3-quart casserole, top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peanut butter.
Cook to soft ball stage.
The mixture will take on a yellowish look in about 5 minutes.
This should be the soft ball stage.
Remove from stove and beat in 4 tablespoons of peanut butter.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan to harden.
Cut into squares.

title: apple wedges
directions: Cut apples into wedges.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over them.
Bake for 20 minutes then serve.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Place roast in shallow pan and roast for 2 hours at 325°. Combine sauce ingredients and pour over roast.
Bake another 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning roast often.

title: alca pulco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add onion and celery and fry also.
Add salt, corn, beans and tomato sauce.
Put in a baking dish.
Put layer of chips, then layer of meat until gone.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: best caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar
and
cook
over
low
heat
for 2 minutes.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and add 10x sugar.
Beat until smooth and apply to cooled cake.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and milk. Pour over cake pieces in punch bowl and stir.
Mix strawberries and glaze. Add 2/3 strawberry mix to cake and stir.
Put remaining berries on top.
Refrigerate overnight to chill.
Serves 50.
(May also be made with peaches.)

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Place ground beef in bowl.
Sprinkle all other ingredients over meat.
Mix together by kneading.
Store in tightly covered container.
Place in refrigerator.
On second day, knead again and place in refrigerator.
On the third day, knead and shape in 4 rolls.
Bake in 150° oven for 10 hours.
Use broiler pan so fat can drain.
After 5 hours, turn rolls over so that bottoms can brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Knead in flour.
Drop onto an ungreased cookie sheet or cut into shapes. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.
(May add 1/2 cup chopped pecans to butter and sugar, if desired.)
Makes 5 dozen small cookies.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put ground beef in saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover meat only.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with lid and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: salpicon(chopped beef with mint and orange)
directions: In a heavy saucepan cover the beef with water, add the salt and bring the water to a boil, skimming the froth as it rises to the surface.
Simmer the beef, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours or until it is very tender and let it cool in the broth, uncovered.
Transfer the beef with a slotted spoon to a cutting board, reserving the broth and chop it fine.
In a bowl, combine the beef, orange juice, 1/4 cup of the reserved broth, onion, mint, lemon juice, pepper and salt to taste.
Transfer the mixture to a serving bowl.
Set in the center of a platter and surround it with corn chips for dipping.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups, serving 6 as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: southern red rice casserole
directions: Brown sliced Rogerwood smoked sausage in bacon drippings. Combine with remaining ingredients. Crumble fried bacon into ingredients.
Mix well. Place in casserole dish. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for one hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and 1/4 cup water.
