Bring to a boil.
Add rhubarb.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add strawberries and simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in roasting pan.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts, mix well. Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients together real good, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add your nuts and raisins.
Pour in oiled 4 pound coffee cans 1/2 full or 6 or 8 No. 2 cans 1/2 full or you can use loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo with stuffing mix.
Mix soups, broth and chicken. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 corn bread mix. Add chicken mixture and cover with rest of corn bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns, and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve on hot toasted buns.

title: fruity yogurt parfaits
directions: Layer yogurt, fruit and graham cracker crumbs in cups or glasses to make parfaits.

title: crusty spam bake
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, brown sugar and cloves.
Cut Spam crosswise into eight slices.
Spread both sides of slices with mustard, then coat generously with a crust of corn flake crumb mixture.
Place Spam and pineapple slices individually in a foil lined shallow baking pan; do not crowd.
Brush pineapple slices with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve on heated platter, placing a Spam slice on each pineapple slice.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix cookies with 1/2 cup melted margarnie.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spoon or cut soft ice cream on top of cookies. Freeze until firm.
Put powdered sugar, evaporated milk, 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate chips in saucepan.
Boil ingredients on top of stove for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool on stove. Spread over ice cream and freeze.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle caramel on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute vegetables, except tomatoes, in oil for 4 to 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, chicken stock, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: giant chocolate chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets or spray with Pam. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat the margarine and sugars in a large bowl with an electric mixer at high speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Beat in vanilla.
Turn mixer speed to low. Add the flour mixture and mix until all the ingredients are well blended.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Drop 1/4 cup at a time, 4 inches apart, onto baking sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight container.

title: christmas punch
directions: Place the spices in a bag of fine cheesecloth.
Peel and cut into thin slices, the lemons and oranges, mixing with the apple cider and pineapple juice.
To this add the bag of spices and bring to a very low simmering boil.
Stir as it simmers for approximately 15 minutes, then add salt and stir vigorously.

title: cheese balls
directions: Shred Cheddar, Velveeta and cream cheese.
Combine shredded cheeses with remaining ingredients, except chopped nuts.
Tear off a piece of Saran Wrap large enough to overlap a custard cup or small bowl.
Form cheese mixture into ball on Saran Wrap in bowl. Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Unwrap and roll in chopped nuts. Decorate with maraschino cherry, if desired.
Rewrap in fresh Saran Wrap.
Store in freezer.
Makes 6 to 7 four-inch balls.

title: pecan pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Karo syrup.
Add butter, flavor and nuts. Stir until mixed well.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate boiled cookies
directions: Put the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a pan and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Spoon out and lay on wax paper.

title: yummy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When done and slightly cool, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour condensed milk over cake.
Cool completely and top with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Bake covered for 5 to 6 hours at low temperature (275° to 300°).
Fork apart when 3/4 done.
Serve on buns with Arby's sauce.
Very good!

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Put in bottom of pan.
Layer rest of ingredients and chill.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla (coconut flavoring is also good).
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes or until it tests done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: fried rice
directions: Put oil, onions and pepper in frying pan; stir for about 1 minute.
Add eggs; scramble.
Add rice.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: two by four stew
directions: Cook ground meat until well done.
Pour all other ingredients into drained ground meat.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes and eat.

title: french onion soup
directions: Add 3 cans soup to large pot.
Peel and slice onions.
Saute in 1/4 stick butter until tender.
Add to broth.
Make a roux of 1/4 stick butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Slowly add 1 can broth, continually stirring.
Add to broth and simmer.
Pour soup in bowl.
Place slice of French bread on top and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: pineapple-apricot oat bars
directions: Cook the pineapple, apricots, sugar, cornstarch and salt together, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Cool.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, and shape into small balls.
Put in open roasting pan and pour the tomato sauce over the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry minute pie
directions: Pour
water over gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries;
stir until berries break apart. When mixture is partially
set,
pour
in
baked
pie shell.
Chill until set. Serve
with whipped cream.	Raspberries can be used also.
Use raspberry flavored gelatin and 2 (10 ounce) packages of frozen raspberries.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Cook meat until soft and crumbly.
Add onions and celery to meat.
Add pepper and soy sauce, mix well.
Add soups, water and rice, mix well and stir into casserole and cover.
In 350° oven, bake 1/2 hour, stir and continue to bake another 1/2 hour.
Remove and top with noodles.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.
(Is more flavorful if made the day before then reheated before serving.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in small pieces or blend in food processor.
Cook squash and diced onion together in small amount of water until they are slightly tender.
Drain off most of the water, leaving only a small amount.
Grate the carrot, chop the pepper and add to squash and onion.
Add chicken soup and sugar; mix well.
Fold in sour cream and 3/4 stuffing.
Add melted oleo and mix well.
Pour into slightly greased medium size baking dish.
Cook mixture with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: duck kabob
directions: You will need skewers.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, strawberries, dry gelatin, nuts, flour and oil and beat well.
Pour into an angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chess cake bars
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg together; press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Pour over pressed mixture and cook for 35 minutes or until done.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl. Combine egg and fruit with syrup and vanilla; add to dry ingredients and mix to dampen.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool.
Cut into 9 squares.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: continental cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Spread mixture in baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Top with egg slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients in bowl. Pour mixture over cheese.
Overlap bread slices on top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated overnight except for addition of bread.
Add bread and bake 45 minutes.
Serve with blueberry coffee cake and cut up fruit.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix as directed.
Crumble cornbread in 9 x 13 pan. Layer as follows:

title: sicilian pizza
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
In a large bowl, stir flour and salt. Add dissolved yeast.
Mix thoroughly.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Shape into ball.
Place in greased bowl. Grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise in draft free, warm place until doubled.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle chocolate morsels over top.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: creamed chicken puffs
directions: Boil chicken 20 to 30 minutes; drain.
Prepare soup with milk; add chicken.
Prepare pastry shells according to directions. Spoon creamed chicken over pastry shells.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Chop nuts fine.
Set aside.
Soften gelatin in water in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, lightly beaten egg yolks, spice and salt.
Heat to just boiling, stirring constantly.
Turn heat very low and cook for 5 minutes, while stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Let cool.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; gradually beat in 2 teaspoons sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold whites and nuts into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into shell.
Chill 4 hours before cutting (better overnight).
Serve with whipped cream and walnut half.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices (3 times).
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and soup alternately in small amounts, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into small loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes.
Let stand 12 hours if possible.

title: e-z 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in pan (13 x 9-inch).
Add other ingredients in order in layers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix all together with hands and/or spoon.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given: pumpkin, eggs,
salt, cinnamon, cloves and	milk.
Pour into shell.
Bake
15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking 45 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.
Cool. Garnish with cream.

title: spread for sandwiches
directions: Blend cheese with enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Spread on bread.

title: giant crisp chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until blended.
Mix with flour mixture, chocolate and nuts.
Shape into 2-inch balls and place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes. Yields 21 (4-inch) cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix both flours, sugar, butter and eggs.
Then add pineapple, cherries, raisins and apples.
Mix. Then add nuts.
Bake at 220° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add onion.
Add crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle generously with Johnny's seasoning salt.
Top with cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: billie's corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grease sides of pan with margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.
Pour margarine into mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown and set (30 to 40 minutes).
Freezes well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain and spread in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Mix in 2 cans cream of mushroom soup.
Add a layer of Velveeta cheese slices.
Cube 5 to 6 slices of white bread and spread over top.
Melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
(Cover for last 10 minutes.)

title: french chocolate cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Melt chocolate gently with the water in
top
of
double boiler over hot (not boiling) water. Should be done very slowly.
Remove melted chocolate from heat and stir
in the
flour,
sugar
and
butter.
Beat the yolks lightly
and whisk into chocolate mixture gradually.
Beat the whites until they hold a definite shape but are not dry.
Fold into chocolate mixture.

title: polish lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles as usual and set aside to cool.
Cut both sticks of kielbasa into 4 to 5 equal pieces about as wide as the lasagna noodles.
Split each piece of sausage down the center until about 3/4 through and fill with Mozzarella cheese.
Then wrap a noodle around the stuffed sausage.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour just enough spaghetti sauce to fill bottom of pan, then place the noodle wrapped kielbasa into the pan and pour the rest of sauce evenly over it all.
Sprinkle leftover cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted and lasagna is hot through.
Serve with salad and your favorite garlic bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: First, mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Then mix soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add to first mixture, then add the grated carrots. Mix and bake in moderate oven about 350° until done.
This makes 3 layers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Beat the sugars, shortening, eggs, vanilla and milk until smooth.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add all at once to egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add oats; mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes, or until light brown.

title: poppy seed sweet bread
directions: Beat all together for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Put in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: world famous chicken wings
directions: Cook to boil.
Marinate about 2 hours.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Roll out on wax paper. Spread with peanut butter. Roll up and place in refrigerator to chill and then slice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover top with pats of butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges (with juice) eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed with electric mixer.
Reduce speed to low for 1 minute.
Pour batter in 2 greased and floured pans, either round or square.
(Can also be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake should be just springy to touch in the center.
Let cake cool thoroughly.

title: lazy person's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice following label directions, but cook for only five minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Pour off all but one tablespoon of bacon fat and saute onion until tender.
Crumble ground round into cooked onion, cooking until meat is thoroughly cooked.
Stir in bacon, rice and half of the salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix well.
Pour on hot griddle until brown.

title: fruit bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into 2 small greased bread tins.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of loaf pan. Mash bananas; set aside. Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, egg, mashed bananas and nuts. Beat 30 seconds. Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes. Cool slightly. Loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove from pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Best if made 24 hours ahead of serving. Makes 1 quart.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: amish pie crust
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl. Cut in lard. Put egg in a measuring cup and add enough ice water to equal 1/2 cup and add to flour. Pack together with hands, handling as little as possible, into a ball. Roll out for a 9-inch pie shell. Fill with favorite pie filling or bake at 350° until light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: In large bowl, mix cake mix, reserving 1 cup for filling, oil and 1 egg until crumbly. Pat mixture up 3/4 of sides and bottom of pan.

title: chicken 'n stuffing bake
directions: Combine butter and hot water; stir until butter melts.
Pour over crumbs.
Toss lightly.
Stir in 1/2 can onions.
Spoon stuffing mixture into 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Press across bottom and up sides to form shell.
Combine soup, milk, chicken and peas; pour into stuffing shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: sugar popcorn
directions: Boil water, sugar and coloring until soft ball stage. Pour over popcorn and let harden.

title: green fruit salad with honey-lime dressing
directions: Arrange fruit on lettuce leaves; drizzle with Honey-Lime Dressing.
Sprinkle with almonds and garnish, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: Microwave ground beef, garlic salt, green pepper and chopped onion covered for 6 minutes. Stir and drain off fat.
Layer the Scruddles over meat, drain liquid from mushrooms in cup and add water to 1 cup.
Add mushrooms, pizza sauce and mushroom liquid. Microwave for 16 minutes, covered with plastic wrap.
Spread 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over top.
Microwave until melted.

title: southern pecan griddle cakes
directions: Sift the flours, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Beat the milk and eggs until well blended.
Add to the flour mixture. Add the melted butter and pecans, mixing just until blended.
Cook on a lightly greased griddle, using 1/4 to 1/3 cup of batter for each griddle cake.
Serve with warm maple syrup.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Put marshmallow creme in bowl and stir in hot syrup. Continue stirring until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla. Drop on wax paper or put in plate.

title: all american macaroni salad
directions: Gently toss together all ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes about 8 cups.
Serves about 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add beaten eggs, cheese, milk, salt, mustard, pepper and bread.
Beat with an egg beater.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
May be frozen.
Great for breakfast or brunch.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; beat 20 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
(Can use 1/2 cup sugar.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, then beat vigorously by hand for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend garlic powder with melted oleo.
The minute the biscuits come from oven, brush with garlic and oleo.
Remove from cookie sheet and serve immediately.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and chop.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Serve hot.

title: pistachio crunch
directions: Crust:
Melt oleo or butter and add flour then add 1/2 c. nuts. Pat into a 9 x 13 baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: corn mush to fry
directions: Heat the water to boiling.
Mix the corn meal, flour and salt with milk.
Pour into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Continue cooking over low heat for 35 to 45 minutes.
Pour into pans; let set until cold (overnight), then slice and fry.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown ground meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain liquid off meat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Before putting meat mixture in pie crust, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of Bisquick to absorb the juices when cooking.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crust is brown.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate delights
directions: Blend chocolate, sugar, milk, margarine and syrup.
Cook until a soft ball is formed in cold water.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Beat vigorously until it can be dropped by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: caesar salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix the garlic, olive oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt, dry mustard and pepper and set aside.
Put the lettuce pieces in a large serving bowl.
Pour mixture over them and toss well until leaves are thoroughly covered with the dressing.
Squeeze lemon over the salad and toss again.
Pour the cream over the salad and toss it again.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese and toss it again.
The recipe makes 4 servings and takes 30 minutes to prepare.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together and then add the nuts and apples.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Not all ovens bake the same, so you may need to test the cake for doneness.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add onion and ham.
Roll into ball.
Roll in cracker crumbs or nuts.
Great with chips or crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, orange, orange zest, cranberries and pecans.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add sugar.
Grind apple with peel.
Grind orange with peel.
(Can use food processor.)
Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches on bottom of greased and floured pan (9-inch). Finely sprinkle brown sugar over peaches.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Remove skins and slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Beat egg yolks.
Add buttermilk, oil and sifted dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into buttermilk mixture. Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep fat heated to 375°.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.
Keep warm in oven.

title: tommie's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Blend together eggs, vanilla and oil.
Sift flour, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Pour egg mixture into apples and mix.
Stir in flour mixture and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Any cake pan can be used.

title: pecan chicken fingers
directions: Place chicken between waxed paper and flatten slightly with meat pounder. Cut each breast into 4 strips. Mix ground pecans, flour and salt together in a small bowl. Dip each chicken breast in maple syrup, then roll each strip in the pecan and flour mixture. Heat oil and saute chicken until brown on both sides, about 3 minutes each side.

title: rose's eggplant marinara over ziti
directions: Saute chopped garlic and olive oil until golden, then add tomatoes, basil, oregano and salt.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Take one large eggplant, unpeeled, and cut into small pieces.
Saute in 1/2 cup pure olive oil until light brown.
When done, combine sauce and eggplant.
Pour over cooked ziti.
Serves 8.

title: johnny mozette
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Add celery, ground beef (I use ground chuck), salt, onion and pepper and let brown.
Combine this mixture with cooked and drained noodles.
Then add tomato sauce, tomato paste and corn.
Mix all together.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: macaroni cheese with dried beef
directions: Cook macaroni; melt butter and blend in flour seasonings.
Add diluted milk gradually.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add shredded or thinly sliced cheese; stir until it begins to melt.
Scald dried beef and add to sauce.
Add macaroni and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first then add honey, applesauce and oil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes a dozen muffins.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add chili powder, cumin and kidney beans; set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on pizza pan.
Put taco sauce on top of cream cheese.
Cut up black olives, tomato, onion, green pepper and pepperoni. After all ingredients are cut up, put them on top of taco sauce, then dip your favorite chips in and enjoy.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Mix in order given, except marshmallows. Spread mix in pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°. When done, cut marshmallows; put over brownies while still hot. Ice if desired.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, milk, salt and egg yolks in double boiler until starts to thicken; then add lemon juice.
Cook until it thickens.
Cool; fold in sour cream.
Place in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: holiday rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn syrup and whiskey.
Combine wafer crumbs, sugar and chopped nuts.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Mix well and let stand 30 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated or confectioners sugar.
Place in covered container and let ripen for several days.

title: carm's italian dressing
directions: Put in blender on stir.

title: mint julep
directions: Take a double handful of mint leaves and crush them well until bruised.
Drop leaves into a saucepan of boiling water.
Add sugar and let boil until thick syrup if formed.
Pack julep glasses full of crushed ice.
Pour 1 teaspoon of mint syrup over ice.
Add enough whiskey to fill glasses.
Serve with a sprig or mint.

title: party pork barbecue
directions: Coat pork with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown it in oil in large skillet using all the flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Add celery, green pepper, onion, pineapple with juice, ketchup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 6 pieces of chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a piece of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Mix 1 can of celery soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over chicken.

title: orange cake
directions: Beat the cake mix, pudding, water and oil for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time; beat for 2 minutes. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil fryer or chicken breast covered with water for broth. Just before it finishes cooking, I add 1 stick of margarine to the broth.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes. Keep an eye on it.
It's done when top is brown.
Center stays sticky.

title: cheese - pork sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls in hand and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 10 minutes. Can be baked and frozen for future use.
Makes 4 dozen.
(But be sure to make plenty, because they go fast!)

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from the cob and place in pan.
Add margarine, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Cook on medium-low heat for 30 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
If mixture becomes too thick, add additional milk or water.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Boil macaroni.
Cut the stick of cheese.
Dice the ham.
Add a pinch of salt.
Check to see if macaroni is ready, then mix it with macaroni.
Wait 5 to 10 minutes to cool.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Chop seasoning and saut lightly. Make roux with flour and shortening. Put 3 quarts of water in pot and bring to boil. Add tomato paste and roux to boiling water. Add seasonings and crabs. Cook for about 1 hour. Add shrimp and oysters about 10 minutes before cooking is finished.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mash the corn to break it up slightly, but do not puree it. Mix in the flour, salt, pepper and sugar.

Beat the egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored and combine with the corn. Beat the egg white until stiff peaks form and fold into the corn mixture. Heat a small amount of butter or oil in a frying pan and when hot, drop in the corn mixture by tablespoonfuls.
Cook until risen and brown on both sides, turning once.
Serve with chopped green onions and accompany with pepper relish.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable tuna pie
directions: Mix egg, mayonnaise, seasonings, onion and pepper.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Mix in tuna.
Press gently in an 8-inch pie plate with back of spoon.
Shape (like pie crust).
Toss vegetables with 1/4 cup cheese; put in tuna shell.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Add honey, margarine, salt and water.
Mix well; then add whole wheat flour and white flour.
Mix until dough is easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and turn so all surfaces are greased.
(I use about 1 tablespoon oil.)
Cover and let dough rise in warm place until double, approximately 1 hour.
Punch down and divide in half. Form into loaves and place in 2 oiled bread pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Loaves will sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from oven; rub top of loaves with margarine.
Cool on wire racks.
These freeze well.

title: butter pecan popcorn
directions: Spray a 17 x 2 x 2-inch roasting pan with Pam.
Place popped corn and pecans in pan.
Keep popcorn warm in a 300° oven while making coating.
Melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn syrup, pudding mix and vanilla.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn. Toss gently to coat.
Bake popcorn, uncovered, at 300° for 16 minutes, stirring halfway through baking.
Turn mixture onto foil. When cool, break into large pieces. Store leftovers in cool place for 1 week.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Rinse corned beef and put in a large pot.
Cover well with water.
Add sliced onion, garlic, cloves, bay leaves, rosemary, sliced green pepper, parsley and peppercorns or pepper.
Cook on top of stove at a slow rolling boil for 3 hours.
When 1 hour left, add sliced carrots; 15 minutes later add cubed potatoes. The last 15 minutes, add the cabbage, quartered.
Cook a total of 4 to 5 hours on stove top.
It is done when a fork goes in the corned beef easily.
Let meat sit for 15 minutes before carving. Cut against the grain.

title: hawaiian delight pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion while macaroni is cooking.
Mix macaroni, 3/4 can of tomato sauce, meat sauce, water and spices together. Put in large 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Place cheese over top of mixture, then pepperoni.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Melt the butter in a large, fairly deep saute pan.
Add chicken pieces, cut into 8 parts, onions and cook very gently until each one slightly colored.
Add mushrooms, pour in the wine, cover and simmer over gentle heat until chicken is done; about 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove the chicken, onions and mushrooms with a slotted spoon and transfer to a heated serving platter; cover and keep warm.
Make the sauce by reducing the cooking juices by half over moderately high heat.
Add the cream and boil hard for about 5 minutes.
Taste the sauce and season with salt and pepper if necessary.
Pour the sauce over the chicken, mushrooms, and onions. Serves 4.

title: taco snack mix(makes 12 cups)
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels, tortilla chips and taco seasoning mix.
Drizzle with margarine, tossing to coat well. Store in airtight container.

title: decorator's frosting
directions: Beat all together.
Can be used as cake frosting, or to decorate cake.
May add water, 1/2 teaspoon at a time, if needed. Also, tint, if desired.
